{"term": "1971", "caseName": "Brooks v. Tennessee", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1971/71-5313", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - March 21, 1972", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/burger4/oral_argument_audio/16446", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "We'll hear arguments next in number 71-5313 Brooks against Tennessee.", "start": 0, "stop": 35.045, "duration": 35.05, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "hear", "argument", "next", "in", "number", "brook", "against", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Summers you may proceed.", "start": 35.045, "stop": 38.511, "duration": 3.47, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "you", "may", "proceed"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.", "start": 38.511, "stop": 42.311, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "I represent the petitioner Donald Brooks who was convicted of the offense of armed robbery on the laws of the State of Tennessee and sentence to 10 years in state penitentiary.", "start": 42.311, "stop": 51.235, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["i", "represent", "the", "petitioner", "donald", "brook", "who", "be", "convict", "of", "the", "offense", "of", "armed", "robbery", "on", "the", "law", "of", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "and", "sentence", "to", "year", "in", "state", "penitentiary"]]}, {"text": "Because I consider this to be a novel question of law, I would like to very briefly spend some time on the facts of this particular case.", "start": 51.235, "stop": 60.012, "duration": 8.78, "cleanText": [["because", "i", "consider", "this", "to", "be", "a", "novel", "question", "of", "law", "i", "would", "like", "to", "very", "briefly", "spend", "some", "time", "on", "the", "fact", "of", "this", "particular", "case"]]}, {"text": "The sole question which the Court has issued has granted certiorari is to whether the -- is on the question of whether the Trial Court was in error in refusing to allow the defendant to be placed on the witness stand after other witnesses testified in his behalf under Tennessee Code Section 40-2403 as said Tennessee statute requiring defendant to be the first witness is unconstitutional in violation of the Fifth, Sixth, and Fourteenth Amendments of the Federal Constitution in Article 1, Section 9 of the Tennessee Constitution.", "start": 60.012, "stop": 91.755, "duration": 31.74, "cleanText": [["the", "sole", "question", "which", "the", "court", "have", "issue", "have", "grant", "certiorari", "be", "to", "whether", "the", "be", "on", "the", "question", "of", "whether", "the", "trial", "court", "be", "in", "error", "in", "refuse", "to", "allow", "the", "defendant", "to", "be", "place", "on", "the", "witness", "stand", "after", "other", "witness", "testify", "in", "his", "behalf", "under", "tennessee", "code", "section", "as", "say", "tennessee", "statute", "require", "defendant", "to", "be", "the", "first", "witness", "be", "unconstitutional", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "fifth", "sixth", "and", "fourteenth", "amendment", "of", "the", "federal", "constitution", "in", "article", "section", "of", "the", "tennessee", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "This question is presented into two phrases and the other section was said the Code Section 40-2403 deprives a defendant of due process of law in violation of the Fourteenth Amendment of United States Constitution.", "start": 91.755, "stop": 105.114, "duration": 13.36, "cleanText": [["this", "question", "be", "present", "into", "two", "phrase", "and", "the", "other", "section", "be", "say", "the", "code", "section", "deprive", "a", "defendant", "of", "due", "process", "of", "law", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "of", "united", "state", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "Now this question, the statute that involved for this particular matter was enacted in Tennessee in 1887.", "start": 105.114, "stop": 115.675, "duration": 10.56, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "question", "the", "statute", "that", "involve", "for", "this", "particular", "matter", "be", "enact", "in", "tennessee", "in"]]}, {"text": "I would like to very briefly present to what matter in which this case -- this question was raise at the Trial Court and to do that, I would very briefly like to direct your attention to pages 1 through 3 of the appendix in which is an excerpt of the transcript of the testimony of that particular trial.", "start": 115.675, "stop": 133.231, "duration": 17.56, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "very", "briefly", "present", "to", "what", "matter", "in", "which", "this", "case", "this", "question", "be", "raise", "at", "the", "trial", "court", "and", "to", "do", "that", "i", "would", "very", "briefly", "like", "to", "direct", "your", "attention", "to", "page", "through", "of", "the", "appendix", "in", "which", "be", "an", "excerpt", "of", "the", "transcript", "of", "the", "testimony", "of", "that", "particular", "trial"]]}, {"text": "From the page 1, my question regard to a motion that Court have decided in the presence of the jury.", "start": 133.231, "stop": 139.484, "duration": 6.25, "cleanText": [["from", "the", "page", "my", "question", "regard", "to", "a", "motion", "that", "court", "have", "decide", "in", "the", "presence", "of", "the", "jury"]]}, {"text": "I know Your Honor of course they submitted for the record, I know what the law is but it is something that I would like to reserve for the record.", "start": 139.484, "stop": 145.994, "duration": 6.51, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "your", "honor", "of", "course", "they", "submit", "for", "the", "record", "i", "know", "what", "the", "law", "be", "but", "it", "be", "something", "that", "i", "would", "like", "to", "reserve", "for", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "At this time of course you realize we have a statute in Tennessee which states that the defendant has to testify first.", "start": 145.994, "stop": 152, "duration": 6.01, "cleanText": [["at", "this", "time", "of", "course", "you", "realize", "we", "have", "a", "statute", "in", "tennessee", "which", "state", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "to", "testify", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "To the Court?", "start": 152, "stop": 152.626, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["to", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 152.626, "stop": 153.97, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers.", "start": 153.97, "stop": 154.632, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would like for the purpose of the record to get to my client at this time, I do not feel that I know whom you want or not.", "start": 154.632, "stop": 160.844, "duration": 6.21, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "record", "to", "get", "to", "my", "client", "at", "this", "time", "i", "do", "not", "feel", "that", "i", "know", "whom", "you", "want", "or", "not"]]}, {"text": "And I would like -- I have two other witnesses, I have another witness, two more witnesses.", "start": 160.844, "stop": 164.627, "duration": 3.78, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "would", "like", "i", "have", "two", "other", "witness", "i", "have", "another", "witness", "two", "more", "witness"]]}, {"text": "I use chief points to put on the stand and I would like to reserve the right to call Mr. Brooks after they have testified.", "start": 164.627, "stop": 170.255, "duration": 5.63, "cleanText": [["i", "use", "chief", "point", "to", "put", "on", "the", "stand", "and", "i", "would", "like", "to", "reserve", "the", "right", "to", "call", "mr", "brook", "after", "they", "have", "testify"]]}, {"text": "If the fact should want and that's my motion I would like to. The Court in oppose it well at this time the Assistant District Attorney General Mr. Donald Pugh interposed who said, \"Sir, we'll waive the statute if you would waive the statute.\"", "start": 170.255, "stop": 183.504, "duration": 13.25, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "fact", "should", "want", "and", "that", "be", "my", "motion", "i", "would", "like", "to"], ["the", "court", "in", "oppose", "it", "well", "at", "this", "time", "the", "assistant", "district", "attorney", "general", "mr", "donald", "pugh", "interpose", "who", "say", "sir", "we", "will", "waive", "the", "statute", "if", "you", "would", "waive", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "The court responded, \"No sir, I am going to follow the law.", "start": 183.504, "stop": 186.233, "duration": 2.73, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "respond", "no", "sir", "i", "be", "go", "to", "follow", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "The law is as you know it to be that if defendant's testifies he has to testify first and so doing the recess you can consider that.", "start": 186.233, "stop": 193.721, "duration": 7.49, "cleanText": [["the", "law", "be", "as", "you", "know", "it", "to", "be", "that", "if", "defendant", "s", "testifies", "he", "have", "to", "testify", "first", "and", "so", "do", "the", "recess", "you", "can", "consider", "that"]]}, {"text": "Do you have anything else to bring before the Court before recess?\"", "start": 193.721, "stop": 196.807, "duration": 3.09, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "anything", "else", "to", "bring", "before", "the", "court", "before", "recess"]]}, {"text": "I made other motions and recess was taken and we came back after short recess and the Court saying further.\"", "start": 196.807, "stop": 202.556, "duration": 5.75, "cleanText": [["i", "make", "other", "motion", "and", "recess", "be", "take", "and", "we", "come", "back", "after", "short", "recess", "and", "the", "court", "say", "far"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Summers, you do want this witness to testify and that you're not going to use the defendant, is that correct?\"", "start": 202.556, "stop": 209.292, "duration": 6.74, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "you", "do", "want", "this", "witness", "to", "testify", "and", "that", "you", "be", "not", "go", "to", "use", "the", "defendant", "be", "that", "correct"]]}, {"text": "In my response, \"Not at this time, Your Honor, I will.\"", "start": 209.292, "stop": 212.029, "duration": 2.74, "cleanText": [["in", "my", "response", "not", "at", "this", "time", "your", "honor", "i", "will"]]}, {"text": "The Court interposes it, \"Well, I want on your motion on that.", "start": 212.029, "stop": 214.778, "duration": 2.75, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "interpose", "it", "well", "i", "want", "on", "your", "motion", "on", "that"]]}, {"text": "So in other words if you intend to let the defendant Brooks testify, you will have to be first.\"", "start": 214.778, "stop": 220.352, "duration": 5.57, "cleanText": [["so", "in", "other", "word", "if", "you", "intend", "to", "let", "the", "defendant", "brook", "testify", "you", "will", "have", "to", "be", "first"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Summers, \"Your Honor, of course I understand the course ruling of this, I would like to the purpose of the record like I explained I would like to later move put him on again if I should decide.", "start": 220.352, "stop": 229.99, "duration": 9.64, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "your", "honor", "of", "course", "i", "understand", "the", "course", "ruling", "of", "this", "i", "would", "like", "to", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "record", "like", "i", "explain", "i", "would", "like", "to", "later", "move", "put", "him", "on", "again", "if", "i", "should", "decide"]]}, {"text": "I'll do without the presence of the jury then.", "start": 229.99, "stop": 232.124, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["I", "will", "do", "without", "the", "presence", "of", "the", "jury", "then"]]}, {"text": "The Court: \"Well, no I have already approved on that but I am just again reminding you in case you have thought about it again.", "start": 232.124, "stop": 238.088, "duration": 5.96, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "well", "no", "i", "have", "already", "approve", "on", "that", "but", "i", "be", "just", "again", "remind", "you", "in", "case", "you", "have", "think", "about", "it", "again"]]}, {"text": "If you're going to use him, if you want to testify in his own behalf you will have to do it now.\"", "start": 238.088, "stop": 243.325, "duration": 5.24, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "be", "go", "to", "use", "him", "if", "you", "want", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf", "you", "will", "have", "to", "do", "it", "now"]]}, {"text": "\"Alright, Your Honors, we respectfully note the exceptions.\"", "start": 243.325, "stop": 246.041, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["alright", "your", "honor", "we", "respectfully", "note", "the", "exception"]]}, {"text": "This is the matter in which this question was raised in the Trial Court.", "start": 246.041, "stop": 249.92, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "the", "matter", "in", "which", "this", "question", "be", "raise", "in", "the", "trial", "court"]]}, {"text": "Very briefly, I would like to read for you the statute which is involved in this particular matter.", "start": 249.92, "stop": 256.425, "duration": 6.51, "cleanText": [["very", "briefly", "i", "would", "like", "to", "read", "for", "you", "the", "statute", "which", "be", "involve", "in", "this", "particular", "matter"]]}, {"text": "In 1887, the Tennessee General Assembly, in part of the entire statute entitled \"Enact to forfeit party defendants in criminal cases to testify in their own behalf.\"", "start": 256.425, "stop": 267.405, "duration": 10.98, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "tennessee", "general", "assembly", "in", "part", "of", "the", "entire", "statute", "entitle", "enact", "to", "forfeit", "party", "defendant", "in", "criminal", "case", "to", "testify", "in", "their", "own", "behalf"]]}, {"text": "The statute is actually two-fold.", "start": 267.405, "stop": 269.077, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "be", "actually", "two", "fold"]]}, {"text": "The first is 40-2402 which gave the defendant the right to become a witness on his behalf.", "start": 269.077, "stop": 275.245, "duration": 6.17, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "be", "which", "give", "the", "defendant", "the", "right", "to", "become", "a", "witness", "on", "his", "behalf"]]}, {"text": "As the second part of the statute which is 40-2403 which the Court has granted, and that means failure of defendant to testify - Order of testimony.", "start": 275.245, "stop": 284.97, "duration": 9.73, "cleanText": [["as", "the", "second", "part", "of", "the", "statute", "which", "be", "which", "the", "court", "have", "grant", "and", "that", "mean", "failure", "of", "defendant", "to", "testify", "order", "of", "testimony"]]}, {"text": "The failure of the party to testify in his own behalf shall not create any presumption against him but the defendant assigned to testify shall do so before any other testimony for the defense is heard by the Court trying the case.", "start": 284.97, "stop": 298.06, "duration": 13.09, "cleanText": [["the", "failure", "of", "the", "party", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf", "shall", "not", "create", "any", "presumption", "against", "him", "but", "the", "defendant", "assign", "to", "testify", "shall", "do", "so", "before", "any", "other", "testimony", "for", "the", "defense", "be", "hear", "by", "the", "court", "try", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "Now the statute prior to 1887, the defendant was incompetent to testify in his own behalf in the State of Tennessee in the Trial Court.", "start": 298.06, "stop": 305.196, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "statute", "prior", "to", "the", "defendant", "be", "incompetent", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf", "in", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "in", "the", "trial", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers, in Tennessee if you push the defendant on first, may he also be use in rebuttal?", "start": 305.196, "stop": 314.116, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "in", "tennessee", "if", "you", "push", "the", "defendant", "on", "first", "may", "he", "also", "be", "use", "in", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 314.116, "stop": 315.144, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And may he be used in rebuttal even though it doesn't take the stand on his own defense?", "start": 315.144, "stop": 319.271, "duration": 4.13, "cleanText": [["and", "may", "he", "be", "use", "in", "rebuttal", "even", "though", "it", "do", "not", "take", "the", "stand", "on", "his", "own", "defense"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, there is a case that is cited in the brief which I believe is Clemens versus State which held that he could testify in rebuttal.", "start": 319.271, "stop": 330.973, "duration": 11.7, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "there", "be", "a", "case", "that", "be", "cite", "in", "the", "brief", "which", "i", "believe", "be", "clemens", "versus", "state", "which", "hold", "that", "he", "could", "testify", "in", "rebuttal"]]}, {"text": "This statute enacted in 1887 in conjunction with 40-2402 is my contention that the purpose of the statute of the legislators at that time was that 40-2403 was to be a safety vow.", "start": 330.973, "stop": 344.334, "duration": 13.36, "cleanText": [["this", "statute", "enact", "in", "in", "conjunction", "with", "be", "my", "contention", "that", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "statute", "of", "the", "legislator", "at", "that", "time", "be", "that", "be", "to", "be", "a", "safety", "vow"]]}, {"text": "Because of this with a new concept in the -- I have cited in brief Ferguson versus Georgia in which Mr. Justice Brennan cites to history in history of the right of a defendant to testify and that this was a new concept in 1887.", "start": 344.334, "stop": 358.64, "duration": 14.31, "cleanText": [["because", "of", "this", "with", "a", "new", "concept", "in", "the", "i", "have", "cite", "in", "brief", "ferguson", "versus", "georgia", "in", "which", "mr", "justice", "brennan", "cite", "to", "history", "in", "history", "of", "the", "right", "of", "a", "defendant", "to", "testify", "and", "that", "this", "be", "a", "new", "concept", "in"]]}, {"text": "This had just been recent enacted in several states for granting to defense the right to testify.", "start": 358.64, "stop": 364.593, "duration": 5.95, "cleanText": [["this", "have", "just", "be", "recent", "enact", "in", "several", "state", "for", "grant", "to", "defense", "the", "right", "to", "testify"]]}, {"text": "In Tennessee, it is my opinion that the reason this was enacted was as a safety vow because it was a fear and it's cited by Whitmore (ph) in the brief and the State relies on it considerably in their brief that it was that -- this would incur perjury that it would give a defendant the opportunity and they would be afraid that he would color his testimony having the right to sit there as a witness after witness standing hearing his own witnesses testify and then mold or adopt his testimony.", "start": 364.593, "stop": 393.841, "duration": 29.25, "cleanText": [["in", "tennessee", "it", "be", "my", "opinion", "that", "the", "reason", "this", "be", "enact", "be", "as", "a", "safety", "vow", "because", "it", "be", "a", "fear", "and", "it", "be", "cite", "by", "whitmore", "ph", "in", "the", "brief", "and", "the", "state", "relies", "on", "it", "considerably", "in", "their", "brief", "that", "it", "be", "that", "this", "would", "incur", "perjury", "that", "it", "would", "give", "a", "defendant", "the", "opportunity", "and", "they", "would", "be", "afraid", "that", "he", "would", "color", "his", "testimony", "have", "the", "right", "to", "sit", "there", "as", "a", "witness", "after", "witness", "stand", "hear", "his", "own", "witness", "testify", "and", "then", "mold", "or", "adopt", "his", "testimony"]]}, {"text": "Now this was the - actually it was raised and the Tennessee adopted the statute in 1887.", "start": 393.841, "stop": 399.229, "duration": 5.39, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "be", "the", "actually", "it", "be", "raise", "and", "the", "tennessee", "adopt", "the", "statute", "in"]]}, {"text": "It is our contentions that this cite in the brief that under the constitutional grounds that this fear of the legislature is not sufficient that the constitutional violation is in the Fifth, Fourteenth and Sixth Amendments of United States Constitution Article 1, Section 9 overcome this and make it imperative that we ask the Court to reverse this conviction and declare this statute unconstitutional.", "start": 399.229, "stop": 424.029, "duration": 24.8, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "our", "contention", "that", "this", "cite", "in", "the", "brief", "that", "under", "the", "constitutional", "ground", "that", "this", "fear", "of", "the", "legislature", "be", "not", "sufficient", "that", "the", "constitutional", "violation", "be", "in", "the", "fifth", "fourteenth", "and", "sixth", "amendment", "of", "united", "state", "constitution", "article", "section", "overcome", "this", "and", "make", "it", "imperative", "that", "we", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "reverse", "this", "conviction", "and", "declare", "this", "statute", "unconstitutional"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "How many of the states have such a statute.", "start": 424.029, "stop": 426.448, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["how", "many", "of", "the", "state", "have", "such", "a", "statute"]]}, {"text": "You know?", "start": 426.448, "stop": 427.164, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["you", "know"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 427.164, "stop": 429.082, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Justice Stewart the Tennessee and Kentucky are the only two states and these are some of the reasons that I would like to urge the point while I am urging that this decision be declared unconstitutional.", "start": 429.082, "stop": 439.516, "duration": 10.43, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "stewart", "the", "tennessee", "and", "kentucky", "be", "the", "only", "two", "state", "and", "these", "be", "some", "of", "the", "reason", "that", "i", "would", "like", "to", "urge", "the", "point", "while", "i", "be", "urge", "that", "this", "decision", "be", "declare", "unconstitutional"]]}, {"text": "Tennessee and Kentucky are the only two states at my research have been able to find and the state agrees to have this type of statute. Now there is of course there is no federal rule and this federal rule that requires this and 18 U.S.C.A. 3481 allows the defendant to testify.", "start": 439.516, "stop": 456.621, "duration": 17.1, "cleanText": [["tennessee", "and", "kentucky", "be", "the", "only", "two", "state", "at", "my", "research", "have", "be", "able", "to", "find", "and", "the", "state", "agree", "to", "have", "this", "type", "of", "statute"], ["now", "there", "be", "of", "course", "there", "be", "no", "federal", "rule", "and", "this", "federal", "rule", "that", "require", "this", "and", "usca"], ["allow", "the", "defendant", "to", "testify"]]}, {"text": "That's the federal statute granting him to accomplish and to testify, there is nothing that states when he must testify.", "start": 456.621, "stop": 462.572, "duration": 5.95, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "federal", "statute", "grant", "him", "to", "accomplish", "and", "to", "testify", "there", "be", "nothing", "that", "state", "when", "he", "must", "testify"]]}, {"text": "This is not the rule in several cases in Tennessee.", "start": 462.572, "stop": 465.167, "duration": 2.59, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "not", "the", "rule", "in", "several", "case", "in", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "A plaintiff does not have to be the first witness.", "start": 465.167, "stop": 467.432, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["a", "plaintiff", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "the", "first", "witness"]]}, {"text": "A defendant, there is no such rule as this is requiring order to testimony in a civil case --", "start": 467.432, "stop": 472.203, "duration": 4.77, "cleanText": [["a", "defendant", "there", "be", "no", "such", "rule", "as", "this", "be", "require", "order", "to", "testimony", "in", "a", "civil", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are there some Court of Appeals that follow this rule?", "start": 472.203, "stop": 477.006, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "some", "court", "of", "appeal", "that", "follow", "this", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor in the -- there is one decision, the U.S. versus Shipp which is 359 Federal Second 185 has held that it is -- held that it was a matter of discretion within the Court as to allow that was not abuse of discretion to allow the Trial Court to control the order of testimony.", "start": 477.006, "stop": 494.621, "duration": 17.62, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "in", "the", "there", "be", "one", "decision", "the", "us", "versus", "shipp", "which", "be", "federal", "second", "have", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "discretion", "within", "the", "court", "as", "to", "allow", "that", "be", "not", "abuse", "of", "discretion", "to", "allow", "the", "trial", "court", "to", "control", "the", "order", "of", "testimony"]]}, {"text": "That is cited the state relies upon that case very heavily.", "start": 494.621, "stop": 498.166, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "cite", "the", "state", "relies", "upon", "that", "case", "very", "heavily"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's the Sixth Circuit?", "start": 498.166, "stop": 499.258, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "sixth", "circuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 499.258, "stop": 500.03, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "I would like to refer to that just for a moment, I believe there is distinction.", "start": 500.03, "stop": 503.77, "duration": 3.74, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "refer", "to", "that", "just", "for", "a", "moment", "i", "believe", "there", "be", "distinction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers, before you do, if you were to prevail here, do you feel you are entitled to a new trial or merely for a remand for consideration of whether prejudice existed.", "start": 503.77, "stop": 516.369, "duration": 12.6, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "before", "you", "do", "if", "you", "we", "be", "to", "prevail", "here", "do", "you", "feel", "you", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "new", "trial", "or", "merely", "for", "a", "remand", "for", "consideration", "of", "whether", "prejudice", "exist"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, we respectfully feel that we should be entitled to a new trial.", "start": 516.369, "stop": 524.839, "duration": 8.47, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "we", "respectfully", "feel", "that", "we", "should", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "new", "trial"]]}, {"text": "I also like to point out that and it's not cited in the brief and I ask the Court because that's only reason that come to my attention that a special committee of the Tennessee legislature pointed by the governor has made direct.", "start": 524.839, "stop": 536.409, "duration": 11.57, "cleanText": [["i", "also", "like", "to", "point", "out", "that", "and", "it", "be", "not", "cite", "in", "the", "brief", "and", "i", "ask", "the", "court", "because", "that", "be", "only", "reason", "that", "come", "to", "my", "attention", "that", "a", "special", "committee", "of", "the", "tennessee", "legislature", "point", "by", "the", "governor", "have", "make", "direct"]]}, {"text": "In Tennessee we are presently studying to revise our criminal rules of criminal procedure to completely revamp the rules in Tennessee.", "start": 536.409, "stop": 546.364, "duration": 9.96, "cleanText": [["in", "tennessee", "we", "be", "presently", "study", "to", "revise", "our", "criminal", "rule", "of", "criminal", "procedure", "to", "completely", "revamp", "the", "rule", "in", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "That a special committee appointed by the governor and the legislature has recommended that this statute be repealed in the State of Tennessee which gives the right 3003 as the second if even a -- either a defendant or the state request it, the judge may exclude from the hearing of trial any witnesses of the first party not the time under examination so he may not hear the testimony of other witnesses.", "start": 546.364, "stop": 570.095, "duration": 23.73, "cleanText": [["that", "a", "special", "committee", "appoint", "by", "the", "governor", "and", "the", "legislature", "have", "recommend", "that", "this", "statute", "be", "repeal", "in", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "which", "give", "the", "right", "as", "the", "second", "if", "even", "a", "either", "a", "defendant", "or", "the", "state", "request", "it", "the", "judge", "may", "exclude", "from", "the", "hearing", "of", "trial", "any", "witness", "of", "the", "first", "party", "not", "the", "time", "under", "examination", "so", "he", "may", "not", "hear", "the", "testimony", "of", "other", "witness"]]}, {"text": "This provision shall not apply to the defendant, the attorneys in the case or the first witness for the state.", "start": 570.095, "stop": 575.696, "duration": 5.6, "cleanText": [["this", "provision", "shall", "not", "apply", "to", "the", "defendant", "the", "attorney", "in", "the", "case", "or", "the", "first", "witness", "for", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "And in the comment that it says the purpose of this Section is to replace the current T.C.A. 40-2403 which forces the defendant to testify first with defense if he intends to testify at all.", "start": 575.696, "stop": 587.172, "duration": 11.48, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "the", "comment", "that", "it", "say", "the", "purpose", "of", "this", "section", "be", "to", "replace", "the", "current", "tca"], ["which", "force", "the", "defendant", "to", "testify", "first", "with", "defense", "if", "he", "intend", "to", "testify", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "It is felt that defendant should be allowed to testify anytime if he wishes and do not lose the right to be heard merely because he does not testify first.", "start": 587.172, "stop": 594.925, "duration": 7.75, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "felt", "that", "defendant", "should", "be", "allow", "to", "testify", "anytime", "if", "he", "wish", "and", "do", "not", "lose", "the", "right", "to", "be", "hear", "merely", "because", "he", "do", "not", "testify", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers, is the rule in Tennessee also with the -- on behalf of the State of the prosecuted witness must testify first if he or she has to testify?", "start": 594.925, "stop": 607.179, "duration": 12.25, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "be", "the", "rule", "in", "tennessee", "also", "with", "the", "on", "behalf", "of", "the", "state", "of", "the", "prosecuted", "witness", "must", "testify", "first", "if", "he", "or", "she", "have", "to", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Justice Rehnquist, there is no statute which requires that but there is appellant there as a case law to that effect.", "start": 607.179, "stop": 614.686, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "rehnquist", "there", "be", "no", "statute", "which", "require", "that", "but", "there", "be", "appellant", "there", "as", "a", "case", "law", "to", "that", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was it committee's recommendation that that be changed too or will it just, the defendant committee recommended the change?", "start": 614.686, "stop": 633.423, "duration": 18.74, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "committee", "s", "recommendation", "that", "that", "be", "change", "too", "or", "will", "it", "just", "the", "defendant", "committee", "recommend", "the", "change"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "They speak - then with the statute this was also discussed under this amendment also Mr. Justice and it held that the proposed section which I read would in fact allow the state to choose a witness that it wanted to help with the case.", "start": 633.423, "stop": 645.839, "duration": 12.42, "cleanText": [["they", "speak", "then", "with", "the", "statute", "this", "be", "also", "discuss", "under", "this", "amendment", "also", "mr", "justice", "and", "it", "hold", "that", "the", "propose", "section", "which", "i", "read", "would", "in", "fact", "allow", "the", "state", "to", "choose", "a", "witness", "that", "it", "want", "to", "help", "with", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "The state would merely put its most helpful witness on the stand first, that is what they proposed under the statute.", "start": 645.839, "stop": 652.962, "duration": 7.12, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "would", "merely", "put", "its", "most", "helpful", "witness", "on", "the", "stand", "first", "that", "be", "what", "they", "propose", "under", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "What happens if they don't? Does the prosecution collapse?", "start": 652.962, "stop": 657.079, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["what", "happen", "if", "they", "do", "not"], ["do", "the", "prosecution", "collapse"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor under the coding of the Smartt case that this is - they would not be allowed to use that witness.", "start": 657.079, "stop": 665.413, "duration": 8.33, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "under", "the", "coding", "of", "the", "smartt", "case", "that", "this", "be", "they", "would", "not", "be", "allow", "to", "use", "that", "witness"]]}, {"text": "That is the only as I understand.", "start": 665.413, "stop": 667.271, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "only", "as", "i", "understand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even though it's a prosecuting witness?", "start": 667.271, "stop": 669.221, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["even", "though", "it", "be", "a", "prosecute", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sir?", "start": 669.221, "stop": 669.884, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even though it's by definition the prosecuting witness?", "start": 669.884, "stop": 672.642, "duration": 2.76, "cleanText": [["even", "though", "it", "be", "by", "definition", "the", "prosecuting", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 672.642, "stop": 674.857, "duration": 2.21, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Doesn't that mean there is no prosecution?", "start": 674.857, "stop": 678.732, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "that", "mean", "there", "be", "no", "prosecution"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that yes sir that normally this case that cited this was the Smartt decision which is derived upon in the governments and the states' brief is a very old case also as all of these cases relying upon this argument.", "start": 678.732, "stop": 695.964, "duration": 17.23, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "yes", "sir", "that", "normally", "this", "case", "that", "cite", "this", "be", "the", "smartt", "decision", "which", "be", "derive", "upon", "in", "the", "government", "and", "the", "state", "brief", "be", "a", "very", "old", "case", "also", "as", "all", "of", "these", "case", "rely", "upon", "this", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "As I understand you, the state need not hear the prosecuting witness to sit at the witness stand.", "start": 695.964, "stop": 702.847, "duration": 6.88, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "understand", "you", "the", "state", "need", "not", "hear", "the", "prosecute", "witness", "to", "sit", "at", "the", "witness", "stand"]]}, {"text": "The person is going to justify that she was the victim or he was the victim, if the state wants to choose somebody else to sit at the trial table, right?", "start": 702.847, "stop": 712.015, "duration": 9.17, "cleanText": [["the", "person", "be", "go", "to", "justify", "that", "she", "be", "the", "victim", "or", "he", "be", "the", "victim", "if", "the", "state", "want", "to", "choose", "somebody", "else", "to", "sit", "at", "the", "trial", "table", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 712.015, "stop": 712.372, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "If it's that person who wants to testify first or not at all?", "start": 712.372, "stop": 717.311, "duration": 4.94, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "be", "that", "person", "who", "want", "to", "testify", "first", "or", "not", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 717.311, "stop": 717.96, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "It's very often they will use a police officer who handle the detective who handles the case and he will be designated as the prosecutor and he sits there at the witness stand.", "start": 717.96, "stop": 726.656, "duration": 8.7, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "very", "often", "they", "will", "use", "a", "police", "officer", "who", "handle", "the", "detective", "who", "handle", "the", "case", "and", "he", "will", "be", "designate", "as", "the", "prosecutor", "and", "he", "sit", "there", "at", "the", "witness", "stand"]]}, {"text": "I'm not saying that this question that you have brought up is not very often raised, in fact many times that prosecutor will not testify or it's not a statutory requirement.", "start": 726.656, "stop": 737.62, "duration": 10.96, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "say", "that", "this", "question", "that", "you", "have", "bring", "up", "be", "not", "very", "often", "raise", "in", "fact", "many", "time", "that", "prosecutor", "will", "not", "testify", "or", "it", "be", "not", "a", "statutory", "requirement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers, maybe you can clear up the confusion for me.", "start": 737.62, "stop": 741.704, "duration": 4.08, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "maybe", "you", "can", "clear", "up", "the", "confusion", "for", "me"]]}, {"text": "In this case when the prosecution rested, do you put on some evidence?", "start": 741.704, "stop": 749.744, "duration": 8.04, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "when", "the", "prosecution", "rest", "do", "you", "put", "on", "some", "evidence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor, I moved --", "start": 749.744, "stop": 751.066, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor", "i", "move"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "None whatever?", "start": 751.066, "stop": 752.709, "duration": 1.64, "cleanText": [["none", "whatever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I did later on.", "start": 752.709, "stop": 754.05, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "do", "later", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "But your first argue, I'm aware that you made the motion, then you put on some evidence?", "start": 754.05, "stop": 758.74, "duration": 4.69, "cleanText": [["but", "your", "first", "argue", "I", "be", "aware", "that", "you", "make", "the", "motion", "then", "you", "put", "on", "some", "evidence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, I did.", "start": 758.74, "stop": 760.641, "duration": 1.9, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "i", "do"]]}, {"text": "I called two witnesses Your Honor.", "start": 760.641, "stop": 763.01, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["i", "call", "two", "witness", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "One of the detective who is prosecuting witness in this matter who had I think in an original assignment there as I raised a confession question and a lineup question which you do not grant certiorari on.", "start": 763.01, "stop": 774.989, "duration": 11.98, "cleanText": [["one", "of", "the", "detective", "who", "be", "prosecute", "witness", "in", "this", "matter", "who", "have", "i", "think", "in", "an", "original", "assignment", "there", "as", "i", "raise", "a", "confession", "question", "and", "a", "lineup", "question", "which", "you", "do", "not", "grant", "certiorari", "on"]]}, {"text": "But the detective who had conducted the lineup which this young man was picked out.", "start": 774.989, "stop": 780.393, "duration": 5.4, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "detective", "who", "have", "conduct", "the", "lineup", "which", "this", "young", "man", "be", "pick", "out"]]}, {"text": "He was not called by the state as a witness.", "start": 780.393, "stop": 783.515, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "not", "call", "by", "the", "state", "as", "a", "witness"]]}, {"text": "Now I called him as a witness for the -- they relied merely upon the identification of the victim.", "start": 783.515, "stop": 789.955, "duration": 6.44, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "call", "him", "as", "a", "witness", "for", "the", "they", "rely", "merely", "upon", "the", "identification", "of", "the", "victim"]]}, {"text": "I called the detective who conducted the lineup as my own witness.", "start": 789.955, "stop": 794.354, "duration": 4.4, "cleanText": [["i", "call", "the", "detective", "who", "conduct", "the", "lineup", "as", "my", "own", "witness"]]}, {"text": "I further called an inmate in the jail who had been -- was in the same lineup.", "start": 794.354, "stop": 798.874, "duration": 4.52, "cleanText": [["i", "far", "call", "an", "inmate", "in", "the", "jail", "who", "have", "be", "be", "in", "the", "same", "lineup"]]}, {"text": "I called those two witnesses that I put on.", "start": 798.874, "stop": 801.76, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["i", "call", "those", "two", "witness", "that", "i", "put", "on"]]}, {"text": "Now, the Court may want -- did I renew my motion after they had testified.", "start": 801.76, "stop": 806.288, "duration": 4.53, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "court", "may", "want", "do", "i", "renew", "my", "motion", "after", "they", "have", "testify"]]}, {"text": "I did not do that and I felt like the Courts ruling in itself.", "start": 806.288, "stop": 809.666, "duration": 3.38, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "do", "that", "and", "i", "felt", "like", "the", "court", "ruling", "in", "itself"]]}, {"text": "I have certainly felt like that it would been improper for me to do so.", "start": 809.666, "stop": 812.951, "duration": 3.28, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "certainly", "felt", "like", "that", "it", "would", "be", "improper", "for", "me", "to", "do", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did the state put on any additional evidence?", "start": 812.951, "stop": 816.076, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "state", "put", "on", "any", "additional", "evidence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, sir.", "start": 816.076, "stop": 817.017, "duration": 0.94, "cleanText": [["no", "sir"]]}, {"text": "They did not put on any in rebuttal after I put on my few witnesses.", "start": 817.017, "stop": 823.737, "duration": 6.72, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "put", "on", "any", "in", "rebuttal", "after", "i", "put", "on", "my", "few", "witness"]]}, {"text": "I felt I had raised this question and two or three other cases and fortunately I got acquittals then and I had one time I had done this before the presence of the jury, I called my move to call him and then of course the Court said no, you cannot put them on and I thought that I did not do in this case because I thought it might been improper because you got it before the jury the fact that why can't, why can't the defendant testify and so I did not do it.", "start": 823.737, "stop": 846.924, "duration": 23.19, "cleanText": [["i", "felt", "i", "have", "raise", "this", "question", "and", "two", "or", "three", "other", "case", "and", "fortunately", "i", "get", "acquittal", "then", "and", "i", "have", "one", "time", "i", "have", "do", "this", "before", "the", "presence", "of", "the", "jury", "i", "call", "my", "move", "to", "call", "him", "and", "then", "of", "course", "the", "court", "say", "no", "you", "can", "not", "put", "them", "on", "and", "i", "think", "that", "i", "do", "not", "do", "in", "this", "case", "because", "i", "think", "it", "might", "be", "improper", "because", "you", "get", "it", "before", "the", "jury", "the", "fact", "that", "why", "can", "not", "why", "can", "not", "the", "defendant", "testify", "and", "so", "i", "do", "not", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "I thought it would be improper.", "start": 846.924, "stop": 849.86, "duration": 2.94, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "would", "be", "improper"]]}, {"text": "I did one time and I thought it might have been improper that's why Your Honor.", "start": 849.86, "stop": 852.925, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "one", "time", "and", "i", "think", "it", "might", "have", "be", "improper", "that", "be", "why", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you spell out for me where the prejudice exist as you tried this case?", "start": 852.925, "stop": 857.801, "duration": 4.88, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "spell", "out", "for", "me", "where", "the", "prejudice", "exist", "as", "you", "try", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 857.801, "stop": 858.853, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "This is very, very simply.", "start": 858.853, "stop": 860.498, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "very", "very", "simply"]]}, {"text": "It is this, the prejudice involves that as you all know and it's cited in Williams versus Florida in Justice Black's opinion with Justice Black's opinion.", "start": 860.498, "stop": 871.601, "duration": 11.1, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "this", "the", "prejudice", "involve", "that", "as", "you", "all", "know", "and", "it", "be", "cite", "in", "williams", "versus", "florida", "in", "justice", "black", "s", "opinion", "with", "justice", "black", "s", "opinion"]]}, {"text": "A lawsuit is not -- you can no matter how hard you compare your lawsuit, no matter how well you know your witnesses know him that's how well you have talked to the government's witnesses or the states witnesses.", "start": 871.601, "stop": 881.095, "duration": 9.49, "cleanText": [["a", "lawsuit", "be", "not", "you", "can", "no", "matter", "how", "hard", "you", "compare", "your", "lawsuit", "no", "matter", "how", "well", "you", "know", "your", "witness", "know", "him", "that", "be", "how", "well", "you", "have", "talk", "to", "the", "government", "s", "witness", "or", "the", "state", "witness"]]}, {"text": "A lawsuit can change and it's our contention that my client to -- that my theory is this.", "start": 881.095, "stop": 887.768, "duration": 6.67, "cleanText": [["a", "lawsuit", "can", "change", "and", "it", "be", "our", "contention", "that", "my", "client", "to", "that", "my", "theory", "be", "this"]]}, {"text": "That to make me choose at the beginning of the trial, I did not feel that they got state and made out our sufficient case in which I should have to put my client on the stand.", "start": 887.768, "stop": 897.167, "duration": 9.4, "cleanText": [["that", "to", "make", "me", "choose", "at", "the", "beginning", "of", "the", "trial", "i", "do", "not", "feel", "that", "they", "get", "state", "and", "make", "out", "our", "sufficient", "case", "in", "which", "i", "should", "have", "to", "put", "my", "client", "on", "the", "stand"]]}, {"text": "My client had no criminal records stipulated in there.", "start": 897.167, "stop": 899.599, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["my", "client", "have", "no", "criminal", "record", "stipulate", "in", "there"]]}, {"text": "It was not -- I was trying to keep him off the stand because he got along with the criminal record which is normally the case.", "start": 899.599, "stop": 905.203, "duration": 5.6, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "i", "be", "try", "to", "keep", "him", "off", "the", "stand", "because", "he", "get", "along", "with", "the", "criminal", "record", "which", "be", "normally", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "But I have, I did not feel that they could -- that I should have to put him on but the prejudice involved is that if doing the course of -- I wanted to put on other two witnesses which would have my side.", "start": 905.203, "stop": 918.026, "duration": 12.82, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "have", "i", "do", "not", "feel", "that", "they", "could", "that", "i", "should", "have", "to", "put", "him", "on", "but", "the", "prejudice", "involve", "be", "that", "if", "do", "the", "course", "of", "i", "want", "to", "put", "on", "other", "two", "witness", "which", "would", "have", "my", "side"]]}, {"text": "The quest -- the problem is that if I put this witnesses on and something happens that they're -- the state in some way affects their testimony and something comes out which can only be explained by the defendant taking the stand then I or on by way of witness stand I am precluded for putting under Tennessee procedure.", "start": 918.026, "stop": 935.061, "duration": 17.04, "cleanText": [["the", "quest", "the", "problem", "be", "that", "if", "i", "put", "this", "witness", "on", "and", "something", "happens", "that", "they", "be", "the", "state", "in", "some", "way", "affect", "their", "testimony", "and", "something", "come", "out", "which", "can", "only", "be", "explain", "by", "the", "defendant", "take", "the", "stand", "then", "i", "or", "on", "by", "way", "of", "witness", "stand", "i", "be", "preclude", "for", "put", "under", "tennessee", "procedure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I know what your theory is, my question is was there prejudice in this case and could you so prove if necessary?", "start": 935.061, "stop": 944.303, "duration": 9.24, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "what", "your", "theory", "be", "my", "question", "be", "be", "there", "prejudice", "in", "this", "case", "and", "could", "you", "so", "prove", "if", "necessary"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, I respectfully submit that the prejudice in this particular case there came up after the Court have ruled that I cannot put him on and then it give up.", "start": 944.303, "stop": 962.346, "duration": 18.04, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "i", "respectfully", "submit", "that", "the", "prejudice", "in", "this", "particular", "case", "there", "come", "up", "after", "the", "court", "have", "rule", "that", "i", "can", "not", "put", "him", "on", "and", "then", "it", "give", "up"]]}, {"text": "I cannot -- the prejudice came up of course not answering because of the fact that I cannot pretty understand.", "start": 962.346, "stop": 969.11, "duration": 6.76, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "not", "the", "prejudice", "come", "up", "of", "course", "not", "answer", "because", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "i", "can", "not", "pretty", "understand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "[Voice Overlap]", "start": 969.11, "stop": 970.234, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, sir.", "start": 970.234, "stop": 971.346, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["no", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, let me follow up on Justice Blackmun's question a little bit.", "start": 971.346, "stop": 975.062, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["well", "let", "me", "follow", "up", "on", "justice", "blackmun", "s", "question", "a", "little", "bit"]]}, {"text": "I take your initial tactical decision was that you got two witnesses you are going to call if they go well so to speak, you're not going to call your own client, then you put those two witnesses on.", "start": 975.062, "stop": 988.001, "duration": 12.94, "cleanText": [["i", "take", "your", "initial", "tactical", "decision", "be", "that", "you", "get", "two", "witness", "you", "be", "go", "to", "call", "if", "they", "go", "well", "so", "to", "speak", "you", "be", "not", "go", "to", "call", "your", "own", "client", "then", "you", "put", "those", "two", "witness", "on"]]}, {"text": "Now, how did they go?", "start": 988.001, "stop": 989.925, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["now", "how", "do", "they", "go"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, in regard to the way that they win, I put on the detective, I put on the detective.", "start": 989.925, "stop": 996.857, "duration": 6.93, "cleanText": [["well", "in", "regard", "to", "the", "way", "that", "they", "win", "i", "put", "on", "the", "detective", "i", "put", "on", "the", "detective"]]}, {"text": "I called him as my witness.", "start": 996.857, "stop": 999.471, "duration": 2.61, "cleanText": [["i", "call", "him", "as", "my", "witness"]]}, {"text": "The Court in Tennessee would not -- the Trial Judge would not to declare him as a witness and I put to him on this question as to the fact that this was a very highly suggestive lineup in which this young man had been arrested for other charges, his picture has been on TV and this detective made the statement that when he called this prosecution witness to come down here.", "start": 999.471, "stop": 1021.858, "duration": 22.39, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "in", "tennessee", "would", "not", "the", "trial", "judge", "would", "not", "to", "declare", "him", "as", "a", "witness", "and", "i", "put", "to", "him", "on", "this", "question", "as", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "this", "be", "a", "very", "highly", "suggestive", "lineup", "in", "which", "this", "young", "man", "have", "be", "arrest", "for", "other", "charge", "his", "picture", "have", "be", "on", "tv", "and", "this", "detective", "make", "the", "statement", "that", "when", "he", "call", "this", "prosecution", "witness", "to", "come", "down", "here"]]}, {"text": "Come on down here, we got the boy that held up the store and my client indicate that he was present when that took place.", "start": 1021.858, "stop": 1029.308, "duration": 7.45, "cleanText": [["come", "on", "down", "here", "we", "get", "the", "boy", "that", "hold", "up", "the", "store", "and", "my", "client", "indicate", "that", "he", "be", "present", "when", "that", "take", "place"]]}, {"text": "This came out on putting on this states witness who I had to call myself because they did not put him on.", "start": 1029.308, "stop": 1035.99, "duration": 6.68, "cleanText": [["this", "come", "out", "on", "put", "on", "this", "state", "witness", "who", "i", "have", "to", "call", "myself", "because", "they", "do", "not", "put", "him", "on"]]}, {"text": "Therefore this situation can only if-the rebuttal of this could only have been by my particular client.", "start": 1035.99, "stop": 1041.027, "duration": 5.04, "cleanText": [["therefore", "this", "situation", "can", "only", "if", "the", "rebuttal", "of", "this", "could", "only", "have", "be", "by", "my", "particular", "client"]]}, {"text": "And my client, I could not rebut this, the statement that when the -- when I put the detective on in question about the lineup and he denied this it could only be rebutted by my client and my client could not take the stand.", "start": 1041.027, "stop": 1052.769, "duration": 11.74, "cleanText": [["and", "my", "client", "i", "could", "not", "rebut", "this", "the", "statement", "that", "when", "the", "when", "i", "put", "the", "detective", "on", "in", "question", "about", "the", "lineup", "and", "he", "deny", "this", "it", "could", "only", "be", "rebut", "by", "my", "client", "and", "my", "client", "could", "not", "take", "the", "stand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did you at that point or at any point in the trial than out of the presence of the jury make it proper of which your client would testify to if he had been permitted to take the stand in the order that you requested?", "start": 1052.769, "stop": 1066.541, "duration": 13.77, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "at", "that", "point", "or", "at", "any", "point", "in", "the", "trial", "than", "out", "of", "the", "presence", "of", "the", "jury", "make", "it", "proper", "of", "which", "your", "client", "would", "testify", "to", "if", "he", "have", "be", "permit", "to", "take", "the", "stand", "in", "the", "order", "that", "you", "request"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor, I did not.", "start": 1066.541, "stop": 1068.04, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor", "i", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Don't you think that would have --", "start": 1068.04, "stop": 1069.8, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "you", "think", "that", "would", "have"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 1069.8, "stop": 1069.994, "duration": 0.19, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- help someone?", "start": 1069.994, "stop": 1070.931, "duration": 0.94, "cleanText": [["help", "someone"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 1070.931, "stop": 1071.496, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "I think it certainly would have it at that time.", "start": 1071.496, "stop": 1074.262, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "certainly", "would", "have", "it", "at", "that", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even if your client had testified first, you wouldn't have been able to respond the detective's testimony.", "start": 1074.262, "stop": 1084.335, "duration": 10.07, "cleanText": [["even", "if", "your", "client", "have", "testify", "first", "you", "would", "not", "have", "be", "able", "to", "respond", "the", "detective", "s", "testimony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir because I -- well I have to put him on -- I put him on as my own witness and of course I have made it in the situation why I would be cross examining my own witness, but I would at least make an attempt to put him on under the statute, I can even attempt to put him on.", "start": 1084.335, "stop": 1099.337, "duration": 15, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "because", "i", "well", "i", "have", "to", "put", "him", "on", "i", "put", "him", "on", "as", "my", "own", "witness", "and", "of", "course", "i", "have", "make", "it", "in", "the", "situation", "why", "i", "would", "be", "cross", "examine", "my", "own", "witness", "but", "i", "would", "at", "least", "make", "an", "attempt", "to", "put", "him", "on", "under", "the", "statute", "i", "can", "even", "attempt", "to", "put", "him", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now I go back to my other question.", "start": 1099.337, "stop": 1100.902, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "go", "back", "to", "my", "other", "question"]]}, {"text": "Supposed you have put him on and then you put the detective on and then you wanted to have him respond to what the detective had testified to, could you then put him back on?", "start": 1100.902, "stop": 1111.551, "duration": 10.65, "cleanText": [["suppose", "you", "have", "put", "him", "on", "and", "then", "you", "put", "the", "detective", "on", "and", "then", "you", "want", "to", "have", "him", "respond", "to", "what", "the", "detective", "have", "testify", "to", "could", "you", "then", "put", "him", "back", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir, not under the State of Tennessee procedure, I could not.", "start": 1111.551, "stop": 1116.702, "duration": 5.15, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "not", "under", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "procedure", "i", "could", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well then where is your prejudice now?", "start": 1116.702, "stop": 1119.881, "duration": 3.18, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "where", "be", "your", "prejudice", "now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Your Honor the --", "start": 1119.881, "stop": 1122.381, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But this is a not guilty plea, was it not?", "start": 1122.381, "stop": 1123.748, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["but", "this", "be", "a", "not", "guilty", "plea", "be", "it", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, it was.", "start": 1123.748, "stop": 1124.614, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I suppose if -- unless he was going to change his plea to guilty if he got on the stand he would have denied the commission of the offense, would he?", "start": 1124.614, "stop": 1132.282, "duration": 7.67, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "suppose", "if", "unless", "he", "be", "go", "to", "change", "his", "plea", "to", "guilty", "if", "he", "get", "on", "the", "stand", "he", "would", "have", "deny", "the", "commission", "of", "the", "offense", "would", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 1132.282, "stop": 1133.722, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And if one can assume that as I suppose it can.", "start": 1133.722, "stop": 1139.256, "duration": 5.53, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "one", "can", "assume", "that", "as", "i", "suppose", "it", "can"]]}, {"text": "The jury might have believe that and then if he wasn't able to get on the stand and testify that he hadn't it, I suppose it's been hard to say that you can't show there's no prejudice in the case.", "start": 1139.256, "stop": 1150.379, "duration": 11.12, "cleanText": [["the", "jury", "might", "have", "believe", "that", "and", "then", "if", "he", "be", "not", "able", "to", "get", "on", "the", "stand", "and", "testify", "that", "he", "have", "not", "it", "i", "suppose", "it", "be", "be", "hard", "to", "say", "that", "you", "can", "not", "show", "there", "be", "no", "prejudice", "in", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 1150.379, "stop": 1151.707, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wasn't that guilty plea?", "start": 1151.707, "stop": 1153.195, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "guilty", "plea"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes it was, it was not guilty plea and he was tried by jury and the jury convicted him.", "start": 1153.195, "stop": 1161.04, "duration": 7.85, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "be", "it", "be", "not", "guilty", "plea", "and", "he", "be", "try", "by", "jury", "and", "the", "jury", "convict", "him"]]}, {"text": "As I stated, they urged various little case law on this proposition.", "start": 1161.04, "stop": 1165.839, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "state", "they", "urge", "various", "little", "case", "law", "on", "this", "proposition"]]}, {"text": "The case is - it's a very new situation where that the abstaining case on fully petitioner is Bell versus Mississippi which is an 1895 case in which this was held that -- this did not rely on the statute but it held that it was an abuse of discretion and improper for the trial court to require that defendant to be the first witness.", "start": 1165.839, "stop": 1184.688, "duration": 18.85, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "it", "be", "a", "very", "new", "situation", "where", "that", "the", "abstain", "case", "on", "fully", "petitioner", "be", "bell", "versus", "mississippi", "which", "be", "an", "case", "in", "which", "this", "be", "hold", "that", "this", "do", "not", "rely", "on", "the", "statute", "but", "it", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "an", "abuse", "of", "discretion", "and", "improper", "for", "the", "trial", "court", "to", "require", "that", "defendant", "to", "be", "the", "first", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that the case relied on by Judge McAlester in dissent in the Shipp case?", "start": 1184.688, "stop": 1188.12, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "the", "case", "rely", "on", "by", "judge", "mcalester", "in", "dissent", "in", "the", "shipp", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, it is.", "start": 1188.12, "stop": 1189.253, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "it", "be"]]}, {"text": "And also the 67 decision of Nassif versus DC which cites the Bell case and the Bell case is being authority and very link the opinion which states in effect that it was still good law, it was a proper rule in 1885 by the Mississippi Court and the DC Court followed it in 1967.", "start": 1189.253, "stop": 1210.328, "duration": 21.08, "cleanText": [["and", "also", "the", "decision", "of", "nassif", "versus", "dc", "which", "cite", "the", "bell", "case", "and", "the", "bell", "case", "be", "be", "authority", "and", "very", "link", "the", "opinion", "which", "state", "in", "effect", "that", "it", "be", "still", "good", "law", "it", "be", "a", "proper", "rule", "in", "by", "the", "mississippi", "court", "and", "the", "dc", "court", "follow", "it", "in"]]}, {"text": "Now, we also -- we take the position that the defendant in a criminal case of this statute is unconstitutional and it denies the defendant the right to testify in a criminal case.", "start": 1210.328, "stop": 1226.496, "duration": 16.17, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "also", "we", "take", "the", "position", "that", "the", "defendant", "in", "a", "criminal", "case", "of", "this", "statute", "be", "unconstitutional", "and", "it", "deny", "the", "defendant", "the", "right", "to", "testify", "in", "a", "criminal", "case"]]}, {"text": "The -- we submit that under this --", "start": 1226.496, "stop": 1230.434, "duration": 3.94, "cleanText": [["the", "we", "submit", "that", "under", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that fully true that he may testify?", "start": 1230.434, "stop": 1234.046, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "fully", "true", "that", "he", "may", "testify"]]}, {"text": "What it denies in is the complete choice of when he may testify?", "start": 1234.046, "stop": 1238.527, "duration": 4.48, "cleanText": [["what", "it", "deny", "in", "be", "the", "complete", "choice", "of", "when", "he", "may", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 1238.527, "stop": 1239.795, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that I go back to my prejudice again by saying that you haven't convinced me I think that there is any prejudice here as to the order of testify?", "start": 1239.795, "stop": 1252.517, "duration": 12.72, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "i", "go", "back", "to", "my", "prejudice", "again", "by", "say", "that", "you", "have", "not", "convince", "me", "i", "think", "that", "there", "be", "any", "prejudice", "here", "as", "to", "the", "order", "of", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Mr. Justice Blackmun, our contention is that we have alleged into this matter that under the Sixth Amendment we are contending is that -- it is been held by the Court that he is entitled to the guiding hand of the counsel.", "start": 1252.517, "stop": 1268.114, "duration": 15.6, "cleanText": [["well", "mr", "justice", "blackmun", "our", "contention", "be", "that", "we", "have", "allege", "into", "this", "matter", "that", "under", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "we", "be", "contend", "be", "that", "it", "be", "be", "hold", "by", "the", "court", "that", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "the", "guide", "hand", "of", "the", "counsel"]]}, {"text": "Now as stated by Mr. Blackmun in the William versus Florida case which stated very briefly that the law changes quite frequently, the -- in the trial of lawsuit which he said that any lawyer who has actually tried the case knows that regardless of demand of pretrial preparation, the case looks far different when it is actually being tried and when it is only been thought about.", "start": 1268.114, "stop": 1290.137, "duration": 22.02, "cleanText": [["now", "as", "state", "by", "mr", "blackmun", "in", "the", "william", "versus", "florida", "case", "which", "state", "very", "briefly", "that", "the", "law", "change", "quite", "frequently", "the", "in", "the", "trial", "of", "lawsuit", "which", "he", "say", "that", "any", "lawyer", "who", "have", "actually", "try", "the", "case", "know", "that", "regardless", "of", "demand", "of", "pretrial", "preparation", "the", "case", "look", "far", "different", "when", "it", "be", "actually", "be", "try", "and", "when", "it", "be", "only", "be", "think", "about"]]}, {"text": "We say that this statute, how the prejudice comes back is that if the pressure -- the burden that it puts upon the defendant and has counsel --", "start": 1290.137, "stop": 1298.313, "duration": 8.18, "cleanText": [["we", "say", "that", "this", "statute", "how", "the", "prejudice", "come", "back", "be", "that", "if", "the", "pressure", "the", "burden", "that", "it", "put", "upon", "the", "defendant", "and", "have", "counsel"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh!", "start": 1298.313, "stop": 1298.437, "duration": 0.12, "cleanText": [["oh"]]}, {"text": "But in this case, what prevented you from putting him on after the officer testified, someone has asked you that before but I am not clear.", "start": 1298.437, "stop": 1305.834, "duration": 7.4, "cleanText": [["but", "in", "this", "case", "what", "prevent", "you", "from", "put", "him", "on", "after", "the", "officer", "testify", "someone", "have", "ask", "you", "that", "before", "but", "i", "be", "not", "clear"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "The statute.", "start": 1305.834, "stop": 1306.707, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "The statute?", "start": 1306.707, "stop": 1307.582, "duration": 0.88, "cleanText": [["the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "The statute.", "start": 1307.582, "stop": 1308.335, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "You could not put them on after the notion.", "start": 1308.335, "stop": 1313.616, "duration": 5.28, "cleanText": [["you", "could", "not", "put", "them", "on", "after", "the", "notion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "The statute precludes, that is the --", "start": 1313.616, "stop": 1316.739, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "precludes", "that", "be", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "The judges, you sense before that they have modified this with respect to rebuttal and answer to an early question of Justice Blackmun.", "start": 1316.739, "stop": 1326.18, "duration": 9.44, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "you", "sense", "before", "that", "they", "have", "modify", "this", "with", "respect", "to", "rebuttal", "and", "answer", "to", "an", "early", "question", "of", "justice", "blackmun"]]}, {"text": "You said that the Supreme Court of Tennessee has permitted and we put on other border or rebuttal testimony only.", "start": 1326.18, "stop": 1337.654, "duration": 11.47, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "that", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "tennessee", "have", "permit", "and", "we", "put", "on", "other", "border", "or", "rebuttal", "testimony", "only"]]}, {"text": "Now that would be to rebut this certain rebuttal is rather could really be, wouldn't it?", "start": 1337.654, "stop": 1345.135, "duration": 7.48, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "would", "be", "to", "rebut", "this", "certain", "rebuttal", "be", "rather", "could", "really", "be", "would", "not", "it"]]}, {"text": "That would come only after the stated put on some new evidence following your defense and then you can put your man on, is that correct?", "start": 1345.135, "stop": 1355.875, "duration": 10.74, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "come", "only", "after", "the", "stated", "put", "on", "some", "new", "evidence", "follow", "your", "defense", "and", "then", "you", "can", "put", "your", "man", "on", "be", "that", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, in the brief the Tennessee decision discusses the question of rebuttal.", "start": 1355.875, "stop": 1363.188, "duration": 7.31, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "in", "the", "brief", "the", "tennessee", "decision", "discuss", "the", "question", "of", "rebuttal"]]}, {"text": "The --", "start": 1363.188, "stop": 1369.465, "duration": 6.28, "cleanText": [["the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did I correctly understand you to say that in response to Justice Blackmun's question that he can be put on in rebuttal?", "start": 1369.465, "stop": 1379.38, "duration": 9.92, "cleanText": [["do", "i", "correctly", "understand", "you", "to", "say", "that", "in", "response", "to", "justice", "blackmun", "s", "question", "that", "he", "can", "be", "put", "on", "in", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I have this one moment Your Honor and think that I can --", "start": 1379.38, "stop": 1382.334, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "have", "this", "one", "moment", "your", "honor", "and", "think", "that", "i", "can"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "[Voice Overlap] go ahead.", "start": 1382.334, "stop": 1393.367, "duration": 11.03, "cleanText": [["voice", "overlap", "go", "ahead"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, in the case of Arnold versus State it was cited in the brief that the case where the defendant was convicted of assault with intent to commit murder in the second degree and this case, the defendant did not testify in the defense proof.", "start": 1393.367, "stop": 1410.756, "duration": 17.39, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "in", "the", "case", "of", "arnold", "versus", "state", "it", "be", "cite", "in", "the", "brief", "that", "the", "case", "where", "the", "defendant", "be", "convict", "of", "assault", "with", "intent", "to", "commit", "murder", "in", "the", "second", "degree", "and", "this", "case", "the", "defendant", "do", "not", "testify", "in", "the", "defense", "proof"]]}, {"text": "Now he attempted the call as a rebuttal of witness which his client - it seems incidentally be called as rebuttal witness to deny that the defendant and his attorney had offered the victim $500.00 to drop the case as the fact.", "start": 1410.756, "stop": 1422.818, "duration": 12.06, "cleanText": [["now", "he", "attempt", "the", "call", "as", "a", "rebuttal", "of", "witness", "which", "his", "client", "it", "seem", "incidentally", "be", "call", "as", "rebuttal", "witness", "to", "deny", "that", "the", "defendant", "and", "his", "attorney", "have", "offer", "the", "victim", "to", "drop", "the", "case", "as", "the", "fact"]]}, {"text": "Now the Supreme Court in that case declined to allow the defendant to testify an objection by the state and of course in our state the Supreme Court held that it was error for the defendant not to be able to be called as a rebuttal witness.", "start": 1422.818, "stop": 1435.875, "duration": 13.06, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "supreme", "court", "in", "that", "case", "decline", "to", "allow", "the", "defendant", "to", "testify", "an", "objection", "by", "the", "state", "and", "of", "course", "in", "our", "state", "the", "supreme", "court", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "error", "for", "the", "defendant", "not", "to", "be", "able", "to", "be", "call", "as", "a", "rebuttal", "witness"]]}, {"text": "So as to the question, he could.", "start": 1435.875, "stop": 1438.036, "duration": 2.16, "cleanText": [["so", "as", "to", "the", "question", "he", "could"]]}, {"text": "I may misinformed the Court that he could been called as a rebuttal witness but the situation in --", "start": 1438.036, "stop": 1445.249, "duration": 7.21, "cleanText": [["i", "may", "misinform", "the", "court", "that", "he", "could", "be", "call", "as", "a", "rebuttal", "witness", "but", "the", "situation", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "At what stage?", "start": 1445.249, "stop": 1446.38, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["at", "what", "stage"]]}, {"text": "Rebutting the states?", "start": 1446.38, "stop": 1448.674, "duration": 2.29, "cleanText": [["rebut", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "The rebutting the states proof yes sir.", "start": 1448.674, "stop": 1450.152, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["the", "rebut", "the", "state", "proof", "yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "At surrebuttal, this is technical sentence though, and wouldn't it had been a proper argument to the state to make if you try to call him on surrebuttal after the state put on rebuttal to answer this testimony that you had brought out on your own case on the defense that this is a legitimate surrebutal.", "start": 1450.152, "stop": 1471.133, "duration": 20.98, "cleanText": [["at", "surrebuttal", "this", "be", "technical", "sentence", "though", "and", "would", "not", "it", "have", "be", "a", "proper", "argument", "to", "the", "state", "to", "make", "if", "you", "try", "to", "call", "him", "on", "surrebuttal", "after", "the", "state", "put", "on", "rebuttal", "to", "answer", "this", "testimony", "that", "you", "have", "bring", "out", "on", "your", "own", "case", "on", "the", "defense", "that", "this", "be", "a", "legitimate", "surrebutal"]]}, {"text": "I mean even though in Tennessee you could testify, your client could testify in surrebuttal, wouldn't the state have had an objection if you try to produce your client on surrebutal on this case just to refute what the officer that have said when you had it understand as drugs.", "start": 1471.133, "stop": 1489.553, "duration": 18.42, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "even", "though", "in", "tennessee", "you", "could", "testify", "your", "client", "could", "testify", "in", "surrebuttal", "would", "not", "the", "state", "have", "have", "an", "objection", "if", "you", "try", "to", "produce", "your", "client", "on", "surrebutal", "on", "this", "case", "just", "to", "refute", "what", "the", "officer", "that", "have", "say", "when", "you", "have", "it", "understand", "as", "drug"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, they would.", "start": 1489.553, "stop": 1490.442, "duration": 0.89, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "they", "would"]]}, {"text": "I am sure that they would have --", "start": 1490.442, "stop": 1492.701, "duration": 2.26, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "sure", "that", "they", "would", "have"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "The officer was your witness as I understand it.", "start": 1492.701, "stop": 1494.701, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["the", "officer", "be", "your", "witness", "as", "i", "understand", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1494.701, "stop": 1495.021, "duration": 0.32, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You weren't allowed to (Inaudible)?", "start": 1495.021, "stop": 1496.857, "duration": 1.84, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "not", "allow", "to", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir I was not.", "start": 1496.857, "stop": 1498.075, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "i", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "In fact I asked the Court --", "start": 1498.075, "stop": 1499.071, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "i", "ask", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can rebut your own testimony and evidence?", "start": 1499.071, "stop": 1501.03, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["can", "rebut", "your", "own", "testimony", "and", "evidence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Correct, yes sir.", "start": 1501.03, "stop": 1502.617, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["correct", "yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers don't misunderstand me.", "start": 1502.617, "stop": 1504.301, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "do", "not", "misunderstand", "me"]]}, {"text": "I don't think much of your system.", "start": 1504.301, "stop": 1506.054, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "much", "of", "your", "system"]]}, {"text": "What I'm concerned in about is whether it's unconstitutional.", "start": 1506.054, "stop": 1510.334, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["what", "I", "be", "concern", "in", "about", "be", "whether", "it", "be", "unconstitutional"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 1510.334, "stop": 1510.732, "duration": 0.4, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "I realize that and we in this matter Your Honor, this Court has under the Fifth Amendment has held that the defendant has predicted under Griffin versus California that the defendant has a constitutional right to remain silent.", "start": 1510.732, "stop": 1531.739, "duration": 21.01, "cleanText": [["i", "realize", "that", "and", "we", "in", "this", "matter", "your", "honor", "this", "court", "have", "under", "the", "fifth", "amendment", "have", "hold", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "predict", "under", "griffin", "versus", "california", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "a", "constitutional", "right", "to", "remain", "silent"]]}, {"text": "Now, and that goes that case was dealing with comment on the failure to testify.", "start": 1531.739, "stop": 1537.632, "duration": 5.89, "cleanText": [["now", "and", "that", "go", "that", "case", "be", "deal", "with", "comment", "on", "the", "failure", "to", "testify"]]}, {"text": "We respectfully submit that this procedure that we have in the State of Tennessee is so far it is in the minority, it is not been adopted by any except in the State of Kentucky, has not been adopted by the Federal rules, it's not the rule in civil cases as I respect would submit that the real issue is this.", "start": 1537.632, "stop": 1557.617, "duration": 19.98, "cleanText": [["we", "respectfully", "submit", "that", "this", "procedure", "that", "we", "have", "in", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "be", "so", "far", "it", "be", "in", "the", "minority", "it", "be", "not", "be", "adopt", "by", "any", "except", "in", "the", "state", "of", "kentucky", "have", "not", "be", "adopt", "by", "the", "federal", "rule", "it", "be", "not", "the", "rule", "in", "civil", "case", "as", "i", "respect", "would", "submit", "that", "the", "real", "issue", "be", "this"]]}, {"text": "In this case is whether the constitution implies or states that the defendant has the right to be heard in any case.", "start": 1557.617, "stop": 1565.912, "duration": 8.3, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "be", "whether", "the", "constitution", "imply", "or", "state", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "the", "right", "to", "be", "hear", "in", "any", "case"]]}, {"text": "We respectfully like to save our time for rebuttal in respect to --", "start": 1565.912, "stop": 1569.729, "duration": 3.82, "cleanText": [["we", "respectfully", "like", "to", "save", "our", "time", "for", "rebuttal", "in", "respect", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your summary just boils down in the part of the record that you read to us.", "start": 1569.729, "stop": 1575.404, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["your", "summary", "just", "boil", "down", "in", "the", "part", "of", "the", "record", "that", "you", "read", "to", "us"]]}, {"text": "The state in this case offered the way of the statute and the Court was unwilling to do so?", "start": 1575.404, "stop": 1580.056, "duration": 4.65, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "in", "this", "case", "offer", "the", "way", "of", "the", "statute", "and", "the", "court", "be", "unwilling", "to", "do", "so"]]}, {"text": "How is -- is it a fairly frequent occasion that the statute is waived by agreement parties in the Court or is it not?", "start": 1580.056, "stop": 1589.159, "duration": 9.1, "cleanText": [["how", "be", "be", "it", "a", "fairly", "frequent", "occasion", "that", "the", "statute", "be", "waive", "by", "agreement", "party", "in", "the", "court", "or", "be", "it", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, this particular matter has been brought up.", "start": 1589.159, "stop": 1592.836, "duration": 3.68, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "this", "particular", "matter", "have", "be", "bring", "up"]]}, {"text": "I brought it up three times prior to this case and I was fortunate in any cases.", "start": 1592.836, "stop": 1597.927, "duration": 5.09, "cleanText": [["i", "bring", "it", "up", "three", "time", "prior", "to", "this", "case", "and", "i", "be", "fortunate", "in", "any", "case"]]}, {"text": "I brought it up last Friday in the case and the state offered to waive it again.", "start": 1597.927, "stop": 1601.804, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["i", "bring", "it", "up", "last", "friday", "in", "the", "case", "and", "the", "state", "offer", "to", "waive", "it", "again"]]}, {"text": "The Court would not allow him to wait.", "start": 1601.804, "stop": 1603.517, "duration": 1.71, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "would", "not", "allow", "him", "to", "wait"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Just as here?", "start": 1603.517, "stop": 1604.198, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["just", "as", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes and they have taken the position now that they were not allowed to waive.", "start": 1604.198, "stop": 1609.324, "duration": 5.13, "cleanText": [["yes", "and", "they", "have", "take", "the", "position", "now", "that", "they", "we", "be", "not", "allow", "to", "waive"]]}, {"text": "Now this has been the position of our Trial Judge there in Chattanooga at the times that I have tried to waive this.", "start": 1609.324, "stop": 1616.675, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "have", "be", "the", "position", "of", "our", "trial", "judge", "there", "in", "chattanooga", "at", "the", "time", "that", "i", "have", "try", "to", "waive", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is this generally regarded as a rule or procedure?", "start": 1616.675, "stop": 1620.252, "duration": 3.58, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "generally", "regard", "as", "a", "rule", "or", "procedure"]]}, {"text": "How do you -- how is it regarded?", "start": 1620.252, "stop": 1622.949, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "you", "how", "be", "it", "regard"]]}, {"text": "Currently this judge treats this matter of substantive along some way?", "start": 1622.949, "stop": 1629.122, "duration": 6.17, "cleanText": [["currently", "this", "judge", "treat", "this", "matter", "of", "substantive", "along", "some", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "I feel that it is more a matter of procedure Your Honor but it has not been raised.", "start": 1629.122, "stop": 1637.862, "duration": 8.74, "cleanText": [["i", "feel", "that", "it", "be", "more", "a", "matter", "of", "procedure", "your", "honor", "but", "it", "have", "not", "be", "raise"]]}, {"text": "This is to consider a statute been on books for this period of time as very few cases has been raised.", "start": 1637.862, "stop": 1644.023, "duration": 6.16, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "to", "consider", "a", "statute", "be", "on", "book", "for", "this", "period", "of", "time", "as", "very", "few", "case", "have", "be", "raise"]]}, {"text": "Now, we have one late decision which came out of Chattanooga and another attorney raised his proposition and at the Harvey case but it was -- based its ruling just on the Clemens case which is old decision.", "start": 1644.023, "stop": 1656.627, "duration": 12.6, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "have", "one", "late", "decision", "which", "come", "out", "of", "chattanooga", "and", "another", "attorney", "raise", "his", "proposition", "and", "at", "the", "harvey", "case", "but", "it", "be", "base", "its", "ruling", "just", "on", "the", "clemens", "case", "which", "be", "old", "decision"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Very well, summaries one last technical question.", "start": 1656.627, "stop": 1659.795, "duration": 3.17, "cleanText": [["very", "well", "summaries", "one", "last", "technical", "question"]]}, {"text": "Are you arguing the Sixth Amendment here as well as the Fifth?", "start": 1659.795, "stop": 1663.716, "duration": 3.92, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "argue", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "here", "as", "well", "as", "the", "fifth"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor the --", "start": 1663.716, "stop": 1665.68, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "And my secondarily, are you foreclosed and more limited grant of cert?", "start": 1665.68, "stop": 1671.453, "duration": 5.77, "cleanText": [["and", "my", "secondarily", "be", "you", "foreclose", "and", "more", "limited", "grant", "of", "cert"]]}, {"text": "Wasn't our grant of cert here limited?", "start": 1671.453, "stop": 1674.421, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "our", "grant", "of", "cert", "here", "limit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, this is -- this by an oversight that this matter when it came up, it was on the Fifth, the Fourteenth and Sixth Amendment.", "start": 1674.421, "stop": 1681.76, "duration": 7.34, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "this", "be", "this", "by", "an", "oversight", "that", "this", "matter", "when", "it", "come", "up", "it", "be", "on", "the", "fifth", "the", "fourteenth", "and", "sixth", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "However, there is a provision and also Article 1, Section 9 of the Tennessee constitution which if I may have read the -- which I think it's similar to the Sixth Amendment in certain respects, the right of the accused in criminal prosecution on page three of the brief and all criminal prosecutions, the accused had the right to be heard by himself and his counsel and to defend the nature and cause of accusation against him.", "start": 1681.76, "stop": 1706.118, "duration": 24.36, "cleanText": [["however", "there", "be", "a", "provision", "and", "also", "article", "section", "of", "the", "tennessee", "constitution", "which", "if", "i", "may", "have", "read", "the", "which", "i", "think", "it", "be", "similar", "to", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "in", "certain", "respect", "the", "right", "of", "the", "accuse", "in", "criminal", "prosecution", "on", "page", "three", "of", "the", "brief", "and", "all", "criminal", "prosecution", "the", "accuse", "have", "the", "right", "to", "be", "hear", "by", "himself", "and", "his", "counsel", "and", "to", "defend", "the", "nature", "and", "because", "of", "accusation", "against", "him"]]}, {"text": "It pertains to speedy trials and should not be compelled to give evidence against himself.", "start": 1706.118, "stop": 1711.188, "duration": 5.07, "cleanText": [["it", "pertain", "to", "speedy", "trial", "and", "should", "not", "be", "compel", "to", "give", "evidence", "against", "himself"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "I know what you're arguing.", "start": 1711.188, "stop": 1712.243, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "what", "you", "be", "argue"]]}, {"text": "My question was whether a limited grant of cert restricted you the Fifth?", "start": 1712.243, "stop": 1716.304, "duration": 4.06, "cleanText": [["my", "question", "be", "whether", "a", "limited", "grant", "of", "cert", "restrict", "you", "the", "fifth"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, I think that probably it should, I have -- we have primarily relying on the Fifth and the Fourteenth Amendments.", "start": 1716.304, "stop": 1724.141, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "i", "think", "that", "probably", "it", "should", "i", "have", "we", "have", "primarily", "rely", "on", "the", "fifth", "and", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "I put the Sixth in but I think the Court is probably correct that we should not be allowed to consider it but I think because of the similarity, I did argue the Sixth in this matter. Thank you.", "start": 1724.141, "stop": 1735.111, "duration": 10.97, "cleanText": [["i", "put", "the", "sixth", "in", "but", "i", "think", "the", "court", "be", "probably", "correct", "that", "we", "should", "not", "be", "allow", "to", "consider", "it", "but", "i", "think", "because", "of", "the", "similarity", "i", "do", "argue", "the", "sixth", "in", "this", "matter"], ["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick, we have only three minutes left if you would prefer not to split your argument so we'll defer it in the morning.", "start": 1735.111, "stop": 1742.713, "duration": 7.6, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "we", "have", "only", "three", "minute", "leave", "if", "you", "would", "prefer", "not", "to", "split", "your", "argument", "so", "we", "will", "defer", "it", "in", "the", "morning"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "If it please the Court I would defer it in the morning.", "start": 1742.713, "stop": 1745.35, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "please", "the", "court", "i", "would", "defer", "it", "in", "the", "morning"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "We'll take you up first thing in the morning.", "start": 1745.35, "stop": 1757.59, "duration": 12.24, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "take", "you", "up", "first", "thing", "in", "the", "morning"]]}]}]}, {"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - March 22, 1972", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/burger4/oral_argument_audio/16982", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Argument now in Number 71-5313, Brooks against Tennessee.", "start": 0, "stop": 14.452, "duration": 14.45, "cleanText": [["argument", "now", "in", "number", "brook", "against", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "You may proceed.", "start": 14.452, "stop": 15.809, "duration": 1.36, "cleanText": [["you", "may", "proceed"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.", "start": 15.809, "stop": 20.013, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Its a privilege for me to represent the State of Tennessee here today in an effort to maintain a statute that our elected representatives enacted some 85 years ago and have maintained until this day.", "start": 20.013, "stop": 34.738, "duration": 14.72, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "privilege", "for", "me", "to", "represent", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "here", "today", "in", "an", "effort", "to", "maintain", "a", "statute", "that", "our", "elect", "representative", "enact", "some", "year", "ago", "and", "have", "maintain", "until", "this", "day"]]}, {"text": "This statute is well known to Tennessee lawyers and judges and has been routinely applied and seldom questioned.", "start": 34.738, "stop": 42.455, "duration": 7.72, "cleanText": [["this", "statute", "be", "well", "know", "to", "tennessee", "lawyer", "and", "judge", "and", "have", "be", "routinely", "apply", "and", "seldom", "question"]]}, {"text": "I believe Im correct in saying that its constitutionality has not been challenged in the Appellate Courts to the State of Tennessee or in the United States Courts until this case and until the case of Harvey versus State which our Supreme Court decided last year sustaining the statute.", "start": 42.455, "stop": 61.107, "duration": 18.65, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "I", "be", "correct", "in", "say", "that", "its", "constitutionality", "have", "not", "be", "challenge", "in", "the", "appellate", "court", "to", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "or", "in", "the", "united", "state", "court", "until", "this", "case", "and", "until", "the", "case", "of", "harvey", "versus", "state", "which", "our", "supreme", "court", "decide", "last", "year", "sustain", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "It is not in the record and I have not known until Mr. Summers brought forward yesterday that some man -- member committee has recommended, not a Committee of the Legislature, has recommended that the Tennessee Legislature both qualify the sequestration of witnesses rule which is now a rule of Court or by decision and also repeal or mend the statute which is before the Court today.", "start": 61.107, "stop": 91.27, "duration": 30.16, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "in", "the", "record", "and", "i", "have", "not", "know", "until", "mr", "summer", "bring", "forward", "yesterday", "that", "some", "man", "member", "committee", "have", "recommend", "not", "a", "committee", "of", "the", "legislature", "have", "recommend", "that", "the", "tennessee", "legislature", "both", "qualify", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "which", "be", "now", "a", "rule", "of", "court", "or", "by", "decision", "and", "also", "repeal", "or", "mend", "the", "statute", "which", "be", "before", "the", "court", "today"]]}, {"text": "To my knowledge no Bill has been introduced to do that but if the -- but the legislature, the legislative branch created this statutory rule and its -- it is its prerogative to change it or to remove it or to retain it if it wishes and I dont see that that particular relevant here today.", "start": 91.27, "stop": 113.376, "duration": 22.11, "cleanText": [["to", "my", "knowledge", "no", "bill", "have", "be", "introduce", "to", "do", "that", "but", "if", "the", "but", "the", "legislature", "the", "legislative", "branch", "create", "this", "statutory", "rule", "and", "its", "it", "be", "its", "prerogative", "to", "change", "it", "or", "to", "remove", "it", "or", "to", "retain", "it", "if", "it", "wish", "and", "i", "do", "not", "see", "that", "that", "particular", "relevant", "here", "today"]]}, {"text": "Id like to remind the Court of something that Justice Cardozo said a number of years ago which we believed to be at the a pro po here.", "start": 113.376, "stop": 122.167, "duration": 8.79, "cleanText": [["I", "have", "like", "to", "remind", "the", "court", "of", "something", "that", "justice", "cardozo", "say", "a", "number", "of", "year", "ago", "which", "we", "believe", "to", "be", "at", "the", "a", "pro", "po", "here"]]}, {"text": "He said to the Court in Snyder versus Commonwealth of Massachusetts, not cited in our brief but at page or Volume 291 U.S. 97 at page 105.", "start": 122.167, "stop": 135.271, "duration": 13.1, "cleanText": [["he", "say", "to", "the", "court", "in", "snyder", "versus", "commonwealth", "of", "massachusetts", "not", "cite", "in", "our", "brief", "but", "at", "page", "or", "volume", "us", "at", "page"]]}, {"text": "The Commonwealth of Massachusetts is free to regulate procedure of its courts and a court with its own conception of policy and fairness.", "start": 135.271, "stop": 145.254, "duration": 9.98, "cleanText": [["the", "commonwealth", "of", "massachusetts", "be", "free", "to", "regulate", "procedure", "of", "its", "court", "and", "a", "court", "with", "its", "own", "conception", "of", "policy", "and", "fairness"]]}, {"text": "Unless in so doing it offends some principle of justice so rooted in the tradition and conscience of our people as to be ranked as fundamental.", "start": 145.254, "stop": 156.75, "duration": 11.5, "cleanText": [["unless", "in", "so", "do", "it", "offend", "some", "principle", "of", "justice", "so", "root", "in", "the", "tradition", "and", "conscience", "of", "our", "people", "as", "to", "be", "rank", "as", "fundamental"]]}, {"text": "And further at page 122, But justice, though due to the accused, is due to the accuser also.", "start": 156.75, "stop": 166.64, "duration": 9.89, "cleanText": [["and", "far", "at", "page", "but", "justice", "though", "due", "to", "the", "accuse", "be", "due", "to", "the", "accuser", "also"]]}, {"text": "The concept of fairness must not be strained till it is narrowed to a filament.", "start": 166.64, "stop": 172.511, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["the", "concept", "of", "fairness", "must", "not", "be", "strain", "till", "it", "be", "narrow", "to", "a", "filament"]]}, {"text": "We ought to keep the balance true.", "start": 172.511, "stop": 178.038, "duration": 5.53, "cleanText": [["we", "ought", "to", "keep", "the", "balance", "true"]]}, {"text": "Justice therefore is due to the accuser, to the victim of a crime, to the people of the State and we ask the Court today in the words of Justice Cardozo to keep the balance true.", "start": 178.038, "stop": 192.666, "duration": 14.63, "cleanText": [["justice", "therefore", "be", "due", "to", "the", "accuser", "to", "the", "victim", "of", "a", "crime", "to", "the", "people", "of", "the", "state", "and", "we", "ask", "the", "court", "today", "in", "the", "word", "of", "justice", "cardozo", "to", "keep", "the", "balance", "true"]]}, {"text": "The balance is all ready weighted in favor of the defendant in a number of well-known ways to the Court and I shall not go into those.", "start": 192.666, "stop": 201.546, "duration": 8.88, "cleanText": [["the", "balance", "be", "all", "ready", "weight", "in", "favor", "of", "the", "defendant", "in", "a", "number", "of", "well", "know", "way", "to", "the", "court", "and", "i", "shall", "not", "go", "into", "those"]]}, {"text": "I will refer to one of them of which is pertinent here that is that if the defendant testifies, unlike all other witnesses, he may not be compelled to be outside the courtroom while other testimony is being given.", "start": 201.546, "stop": 220.351, "duration": 18.81, "cleanText": [["i", "will", "refer", "to", "one", "of", "them", "of", "which", "be", "pertinent", "here", "that", "be", "that", "if", "the", "defendant", "testifies", "unlike", "all", "other", "witness", "he", "may", "not", "be", "compel", "to", "be", "outside", "the", "courtroom", "while", "other", "testimony", "be", "be", "give"]]}, {"text": "The petitioner here would like to be favored even further.", "start": 220.351, "stop": 224.74, "duration": 4.39, "cleanText": [["the", "petitioner", "here", "would", "like", "to", "be", "favor", "even", "far"]]}, {"text": "He would like uniquely among all the witnesses to be able after sitting in the courtroom and hearing the testimony of his own witnesses to be able to follow him to the stand and to testify in conformity to what theyve stated.", "start": 224.74, "stop": 240.654, "duration": 15.91, "cleanText": [["he", "would", "like", "uniquely", "among", "all", "the", "witness", "to", "be", "able", "after", "sit", "in", "the", "courtroom", "and", "hear", "the", "testimony", "of", "his", "own", "witness", "to", "be", "able", "to", "follow", "him", "to", "the", "stand", "and", "to", "testify", "in", "conformity", "to", "what", "they", "have", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Its not really unique because thats what is done in 48 states of the Union, isnt it?", "start": 240.654, "stop": 245.915, "duration": 5.26, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "really", "unique", "because", "that", "be", "what", "be", "do", "in", "state", "of", "the", "union", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well its not unique.", "start": 245.915, "stop": 248.134, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "not", "unique"]]}, {"text": "It is done in 48 states but a -- unique among the witnesses, he is the only one who can do that.", "start": 248.134, "stop": 254.566, "duration": 6.43, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "do", "in", "state", "but", "a", "unique", "among", "the", "witness", "he", "be", "the", "only", "one", "who", "can", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "And he would like to be able to do that in Tennessee.", "start": 254.566, "stop": 259.093, "duration": 4.53, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "would", "like", "to", "be", "able", "to", "do", "that", "in", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "But to proceed under the sequestration of witnesses rule, none of the states witnesses has that privilege or is favored as this petitioner seeks to be in Tennessee, not even the prosecuting witness.", "start": 259.093, "stop": 276.015, "duration": 16.92, "cleanText": [["but", "to", "proceed", "under", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "none", "of", "the", "state", "s", "witness", "have", "that", "privilege", "or", "be", "favor", "as", "this", "petitioner", "seek", "to", "be", "in", "tennessee", "not", "even", "the", "prosecuting", "witness"]]}, {"text": "Thus a citizen may be assaulted and robbed or raped and as the prosecuting witness, he or she may not under the sequestration rule remain in the courtroom and hear the other witnesses for the state before testifying.", "start": 276.015, "stop": 293.184, "duration": 17.17, "cleanText": [["thus", "a", "citizen", "may", "be", "assault", "and", "rob", "or", "rap", "and", "as", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "he", "or", "she", "may", "not", "under", "the", "sequestration", "rule", "remain", "in", "the", "courtroom", "and", "hear", "the", "other", "witness", "for", "the", "state", "before", "testify"]]}, {"text": "Now, in order for the prosecuting witness to be in the test -- in the Courtroom and to assist the District Attorney General in putting all of the states file to the case, the prosecuting witness must go on first.", "start": 293.184, "stop": 306.218, "duration": 13.03, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "order", "for", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "to", "be", "in", "the", "test", "in", "the", "courtroom", "and", "to", "assist", "the", "district", "attorney", "general", "in", "put", "all", "of", "the", "state", "s", "file", "to", "the", "case", "the", "prosecute", "witness", "must", "go", "on", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick, so supposing in a Tennessee trial that the defendant does take the stand as the first of the defense witnesses then other defense witnesses are called in, one of those witnesses deals with a factual element which the defendant did not deal with in his testimony.", "start": 306.218, "stop": 328.767, "duration": 22.55, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "so", "suppose", "in", "a", "tennessee", "trial", "that", "the", "defendant", "do", "take", "the", "stand", "as", "the", "first", "of", "the", "defense", "witness", "then", "other", "defense", "witness", "be", "call", "in", "one", "of", "those", "witness", "deal", "with", "a", "factual", "element", "which", "the", "defendant", "do", "not", "deal", "with", "in", "his", "testimony"]]}, {"text": "Could the counsel for the defense then recall the defendant to deal with that particular point as a part of defense case or does discretion exist in the trial judge to permit that?", "start": 328.767, "stop": 340.555, "duration": 11.79, "cleanText": [["could", "the", "counsel", "for", "the", "defense", "then", "recall", "the", "defendant", "to", "deal", "with", "that", "particular", "point", "as", "a", "part", "of", "defense", "case", "or", "do", "discretion", "exist", "in", "the", "trial", "judge", "to", "permit", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Justice, we dont have any decisions on that point but its my opinion that that could be done.", "start": 340.555, "stop": 349.249, "duration": 8.69, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "we", "do", "not", "have", "any", "decision", "on", "that", "point", "but", "it", "be", "my", "opinion", "that", "that", "could", "be", "do"]]}, {"text": "While it may not, the people of Tennessee through their duly elected representatives enact and maintain a statute which requires in at least to this area that the defense be subject to the same procedure of requirements as the prosecution.", "start": 349.249, "stop": 368.473, "duration": 19.22, "cleanText": [["while", "it", "may", "not", "the", "people", "of", "tennessee", "through", "their", "duly", "elect", "representative", "enact", "and", "maintain", "a", "statute", "which", "require", "in", "at", "least", "to", "this", "area", "that", "the", "defense", "be", "subject", "to", "the", "same", "procedure", "of", "requirement", "as", "the", "prosecution"]]}, {"text": "That the accused, that he has to testify like the prosecuting witness who testifies and remains in the courtroom must testify first for his side.", "start": 368.473, "stop": 379.609, "duration": 11.14, "cleanText": [["that", "the", "accuse", "that", "he", "have", "to", "testify", "like", "the", "prosecute", "witness", "who", "testify", "and", "remain", "in", "the", "courtroom", "must", "testify", "first", "for", "his", "side"]]}, {"text": "While in the name of truth and justice and to keep the balance true, many of the people of the state not require that.", "start": 379.609, "stop": 389.259, "duration": 9.65, "cleanText": [["while", "in", "the", "name", "of", "truth", "and", "justice", "and", "to", "keep", "the", "balance", "true", "many", "of", "the", "people", "of", "the", "state", "not", "require", "that"]]}, {"text": "The Court may --", "start": 389.259, "stop": 390.197, "duration": 0.94, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "may"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Could it be that the constitution required that defendant be in Court?", "start": 390.197, "stop": 395.156, "duration": 4.96, "cleanText": [["could", "it", "be", "that", "the", "constitution", "require", "that", "defendant", "be", "in", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, indeed it does Mr. Justice.", "start": 395.156, "stop": 396.71, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["yes", "indeed", "it", "do", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "And it doesnt require to prosecuting witness being in there?", "start": 396.71, "stop": 399.111, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "do", "not", "require", "to", "prosecute", "witness", "be", "in", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It does not and thats what -- thats part of the problem of course.", "start": 399.111, "stop": 403.397, "duration": 4.29, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "and", "that", "be", "what", "that", "be", "part", "of", "the", "problem", "of", "course"]]}, {"text": "That the defendant and I referred that a moment ago that the defendant has the right, he is favored in that way and we are not contesting it to be on the courtroom.", "start": 403.397, "stop": 412.298, "duration": 8.9, "cleanText": [["that", "the", "defendant", "and", "i", "refer", "that", "a", "moment", "ago", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "the", "right", "he", "be", "favor", "in", "that", "way", "and", "we", "be", "not", "contest", "it", "to", "be", "on", "the", "courtroom"]]}, {"text": "But under the sequestration of witnesses rule, the prosecuting witness may not be there and do the same thing and hear the other witnesses for his side and then testify.", "start": 412.298, "stop": 423.273, "duration": 10.98, "cleanText": [["but", "under", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "the", "prosecute", "witness", "may", "not", "be", "there", "and", "do", "the", "same", "thing", "and", "hear", "the", "other", "witness", "for", "his", "side", "and", "then", "testify"]]}, {"text": "If he is to test -- to be there, he has to testify first.", "start": 423.273, "stop": 427.817, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "be", "to", "test", "to", "be", "there", "he", "have", "to", "testify", "first"]]}, {"text": "Now this is closely connected of course with the sequestration of witnesses rule and all we submit that all the policy arguments and statements that favor the sequestration of witnesses rule argued in favor of the Tennessee statute.", "start": 427.817, "stop": 447.524, "duration": 19.71, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "be", "closely", "connect", "of", "course", "with", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "and", "all", "we", "submit", "that", "all", "the", "policy", "argument", "and", "statement", "that", "favor", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "argue", "in", "favor", "of", "the", "tennessee", "statute"]]}, {"text": "To make the sequestration of witnesses rule more effective, some states in fact this object the parties to that rule in several cases.", "start": 447.524, "stop": 457.892, "duration": 10.37, "cleanText": [["to", "make", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule", "more", "effective", "some", "state", "in", "fact", "this", "object", "the", "party", "to", "that", "rule", "in", "several", "case"]]}, {"text": "And a number of courts in several cases have required the parties to testify first.", "start": 457.892, "stop": 464.844, "duration": 6.95, "cleanText": [["and", "a", "number", "of", "court", "in", "several", "case", "have", "require", "the", "party", "to", "testify", "first"]]}, {"text": "We note this on page 7 of our brief.", "start": 464.844, "stop": 467.648, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["we", "note", "this", "on", "page", "of", "our", "brief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you know when it was in Tennessee, that defendants were -- became privileged to testify?", "start": 467.648, "stop": 473.549, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "know", "when", "it", "be", "in", "tennessee", "that", "defendant", "we", "be", "become", "privileged", "to", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It stated I think in the brief for the petitioner but I dont have that date in mind, no sir.", "start": 473.549, "stop": 479.07, "duration": 5.52, "cleanText": [["it", "state", "i", "think", "in", "the", "brief", "for", "the", "petitioner", "but", "i", "do", "not", "have", "that", "date", "in", "mind", "no", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Its 1887 wasnt it when the statute came in, thats what we are told yesterday.", "start": 479.07, "stop": 483.743, "duration": 4.67, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "be", "not", "it", "when", "the", "statute", "come", "in", "that", "be", "what", "we", "be", "tell", "yesterday"]]}, {"text": "Up until the --", "start": 483.743, "stop": 484.991, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["up", "until", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think perhaps --", "start": 484.991, "stop": 485.954, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "perhaps"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- the late 19th century, defendants couldnt testify at all and when they were permitted to testify this condition was put on and its remained ever since.", "start": 485.954, "stop": 493.928, "duration": 7.97, "cleanText": [["the", "late", "th", "century", "defendant", "could", "not", "testify", "at", "all", "and", "when", "they", "we", "be", "permit", "to", "testify", "this", "condition", "be", "put", "on", "and", "it", "be", "remain", "ever", "since"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats perhaps is right, I think thats right.", "start": 493.928, "stop": 497.783, "duration": 3.86, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "perhaps", "be", "right", "i", "think", "that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And its never been changed?", "start": 497.783, "stop": 499.311, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "never", "be", "change"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Never, never been changed in the state, never to my knowledge been challenged until over the last year or two and I think, and that definitely go even further, it is not being challenged anywhere except in the City of Chattanooga and balance, Summers says, has got in here.", "start": 499.311, "stop": 515.059, "duration": 15.75, "cleanText": [["never", "never", "be", "change", "in", "the", "state", "never", "to", "my", "knowledge", "be", "challenge", "until", "over", "the", "last", "year", "or", "two", "and", "i", "think", "and", "that", "definitely", "go", "even", "far", "it", "be", "not", "be", "challenge", "anywhere", "except", "in", "the", "city", "of", "chattanooga", "and", "balance", "summer", "say", "have", "get", "in", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now its being challenged here?", "start": 515.059, "stop": 516.591, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["now", "it", "be", "be", "challenge", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir and it by the -- and Ill get to this in a moment.", "start": 516.591, "stop": 521.945, "duration": 5.35, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "and", "it", "by", "the", "and", "I", "will", "get", "to", "this", "in", "a", "moment"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Summers in err -- is in error in saying only the Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals has sustained such a rule in the Federal District Court as we point out in our brief.", "start": 521.945, "stop": 531.569, "duration": 9.62, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "in", "err", "be", "in", "error", "in", "say", "only", "the", "sixth", "circuit", "court", "of", "appeal", "have", "sustain", "such", "a", "rule", "in", "the", "federal", "district", "court", "as", "we", "point", "out", "in", "our", "brief"]]}, {"text": "The Ninth Circuit has also sustained that procedure in the Federal District Court.", "start": 531.569, "stop": 539.462, "duration": 7.89, "cleanText": [["the", "ninth", "circuit", "have", "also", "sustain", "that", "procedure", "in", "the", "federal", "district", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you think the defendant has a constitutional right to testify in his own behalf?", "start": 539.462, "stop": 546.495, "duration": 7.03, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "think", "the", "defendant", "have", "a", "constitutional", "right", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "He has that right in Tennessee, he needs -- has it by the statute, I dont think thats really an issue.", "start": 546.495, "stop": 556.248, "duration": 9.75, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "that", "right", "in", "tennessee", "he", "need", "have", "it", "by", "the", "statute", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "be", "really", "an", "issue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Ferguson against Georgia, I think held whatever that he does, doesnt it -- didnt he?", "start": 556.248, "stop": 560.038, "duration": 3.79, "cleanText": [["ferguson", "against", "georgia", "i", "think", "hold", "whatever", "that", "he", "do", "do", "not", "it", "do", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "That the -- that his counsel has the right to direct a statement and to have to do that of the defendant and I would not follow that.", "start": 560.038, "stop": 569.519, "duration": 9.48, "cleanText": [["that", "the", "that", "his", "counsel", "have", "the", "right", "to", "direct", "a", "statement", "and", "to", "have", "to", "do", "that", "of", "the", "defendant", "and", "i", "would", "not", "follow", "that"]]}, {"text": "We certainly believe the defendant ought to be to testify in his own behalf and our statutes provide that.", "start": 569.519, "stop": 575.108, "duration": 5.59, "cleanText": [["we", "certainly", "believe", "the", "defendant", "ought", "to", "be", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf", "and", "our", "statute", "provide", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you claim hes on conditional right to some extent?", "start": 575.108, "stop": 578.92, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "claim", "he", "be", "on", "conditional", "right", "to", "some", "extent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, its simply a matter of procedure to Hogan which these witnesses go on.", "start": 578.92, "stop": 586.137, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "simply", "a", "matter", "of", "procedure", "to", "hogan", "which", "these", "witness", "go", "on"]]}, {"text": "Farther --", "start": 586.137, "stop": 586.731, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["farther"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Whats the rule in Tennessee if a witness to the group thats sequestered testifies and then hears four or five other witnesses and then is asked to re-testify, is that discretionary with the Court?", "start": 586.731, "stop": 599.934, "duration": 13.2, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "rule", "in", "tennessee", "if", "a", "witness", "to", "the", "group", "that", "be", "sequester", "testifies", "and", "then", "hear", "four", "or", "five", "other", "witness", "and", "then", "be", "ask", "to", "re", "testify", "be", "that", "discretionary", "with", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 599.934, "stop": 602.267, "duration": 2.33, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But it was not discretionary here because in this case, the man has and he was denied that right because of the statute.", "start": 602.267, "stop": 611.85, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "not", "discretionary", "here", "because", "in", "this", "case", "the", "man", "have", "and", "he", "be", "deny", "that", "right", "because", "of", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 611.85, "stop": 612.436, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "Thats the way that the trial court viewed it and the statute reads somewhat in that way although our Appellate Courts have been some what liberal in the interpretation of it in permitting the defendant to testify on rebuttal even when he hasnt testified on the writ or in the main part of the case.", "start": 612.436, "stop": 637.058, "duration": 24.62, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "way", "that", "the", "trial", "court", "view", "it", "and", "the", "statute", "read", "somewhat", "in", "that", "way", "although", "our", "appellate", "court", "have", "be", "some", "what", "liberal", "in", "the", "interpretation", "of", "it", "in", "permit", "the", "defendant", "to", "testify", "on", "rebuttal", "even", "when", "he", "have", "not", "testify", "on", "the", "writ", "or", "in", "the", "main", "part", "of", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where he hasnt testified?", "start": 637.058, "stop": 638.673, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["where", "he", "have", "not", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 638.673, "stop": 639.514, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "What case is that?", "start": 639.514, "stop": 640.79, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["what", "case", "be", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats Martin versus State, 151 Tennessee 383, its cited in our brief.", "start": 640.79, "stop": 655.277, "duration": 14.49, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "martin", "versus", "state", "tennessee", "it", "be", "cite", "in", "our", "brief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But what did it do with the statute? Did the stat -- did the Court ignored the statute?", "start": 655.277, "stop": 661.612, "duration": 6.33, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "do", "it", "do", "with", "the", "statute"], ["do", "the", "stat", "do", "the", "court", "ignore", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, sir, the -- its been relaxed or that decision to the extent that that although it appears to read in mandatory language, the parties may waive it or the -- and the defendant is permitted to testify in rebuttal.", "start": 661.612, "stop": 681.198, "duration": 19.59, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "the", "it", "be", "be", "relaxed", "or", "that", "decision", "to", "the", "extent", "that", "that", "although", "it", "appear", "to", "read", "in", "mandatory", "language", "the", "party", "may", "waive", "it", "or", "the", "and", "the", "defendant", "be", "permit", "to", "testify", "in", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "It wasnt relaxed in this case?", "start": 681.198, "stop": 683.019, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "relax", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sir?", "start": 683.019, "stop": 683.45, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was not relaxed in this case?", "start": 683.45, "stop": 685.772, "duration": 2.32, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "relax", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of the -- the defendant wanted to go on first and the Court would not let him do that, thats right.", "start": 685.772, "stop": 691.744, "duration": 5.97, "cleanText": [["of", "the", "the", "defendant", "want", "to", "go", "on", "first", "and", "the", "court", "would", "not", "let", "him", "do", "that", "that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 691.744, "stop": 691.976, "duration": 0.23, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "He did not want to go on first.", "start": 691.976, "stop": 693.309, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "want", "to", "go", "on", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Im sorry.", "start": 693.309, "stop": 693.721, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "[Laughter] What I mean, the Supreme Court --", "start": 693.721, "stop": 695.652, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["laughter", "what", "i", "mean", "the", "supreme", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats a slip, he did not want to go on first.", "start": 695.652, "stop": 697.201, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "slip", "he", "do", "not", "want", "to", "go", "on", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the Supreme Court of Tennessee upheld that.", "start": 697.201, "stop": 700.659, "duration": 3.46, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "tennessee", "upheld", "that"]]}, {"text": "Thats for his faith to go on first --", "start": 700.659, "stop": 702.52, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "for", "his", "faith", "to", "go", "on", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The Supreme Court --", "start": 702.52, "stop": 702.772, "duration": 0.25, "cleanText": [["the", "supreme", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- precluded him from testifying any time?", "start": 702.772, "stop": 707.217, "duration": 4.44, "cleanText": [["preclude", "him", "from", "testify", "any", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The Supreme Court denied certiorari and the Court of Criminal Appeals sustained the decision to the trial court that the statute did not permit him to go on at a later time.", "start": 707.217, "stop": 720.312, "duration": 13.1, "cleanText": [["the", "supreme", "court", "deny", "certiorari", "and", "the", "court", "of", "criminal", "appeal", "sustain", "the", "decision", "to", "the", "trial", "court", "that", "the", "statute", "do", "not", "permit", "him", "to", "go", "on", "at", "a", "late", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "My whole point is that all these other decisions do not help this case?", "start": 720.312, "stop": 725.083, "duration": 4.77, "cleanText": [["my", "whole", "point", "be", "that", "all", "these", "other", "decision", "do", "not", "help", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "They were not -- I dont know whether they were invoked by anyone.", "start": 725.083, "stop": 727.827, "duration": 2.74, "cleanText": [["they", "we", "be", "not", "i", "do", "not", "know", "whether", "they", "we", "be", "invoke", "by", "anyone"]]}, {"text": "They werent referred to and its true that the defendant was not able to go on out of order.", "start": 727.827, "stop": 732.766, "duration": 4.94, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "not", "refer", "to", "and", "it", "be", "true", "that", "the", "defendant", "be", "not", "able", "to", "go", "on", "out", "of", "order"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, how does -- the other cases of relaxation help this claim?", "start": 732.766, "stop": 737.15, "duration": 4.38, "cleanText": [["well", "how", "do", "the", "other", "case", "of", "relaxation", "help", "this", "claim"]]}, {"text": "Not at all, right?", "start": 737.15, "stop": 739.899, "duration": 2.75, "cleanText": [["not", "at", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "He did not get what he wanted.", "start": 739.899, "stop": 744.574, "duration": 4.67, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "get", "what", "he", "want"]]}, {"text": "I would like to refer the Court to the fact and how important this is, I dont know that this is not unique in Tennessee.", "start": 744.574, "stop": 754.446, "duration": 9.87, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "refer", "the", "court", "to", "the", "fact", "and", "how", "important", "this", "be", "i", "do", "not", "know", "that", "this", "be", "not", "unique", "in", "tennessee"]]}, {"text": "Its all ready been alluded to that the State of Kentucky has a similar statute thats been on the books for 79 years and to my knowledge has not been challenged the question as to its constitutionality.", "start": 754.446, "stop": 770.117, "duration": 15.67, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "all", "ready", "be", "allude", "to", "that", "the", "state", "of", "kentucky", "have", "a", "similar", "statute", "that", "be", "be", "on", "the", "book", "for", "year", "and", "to", "my", "knowledge", "have", "not", "be", "challenge", "the", "question", "as", "to", "its", "constitutionality"]]}, {"text": "The Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit, the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit, five of the six judges in those cases that heard those cases approved the rule in the Federal District Courts, it is a rule --", "start": 770.117, "stop": 786.006, "duration": 15.89, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "of", "appeal", "for", "the", "sixth", "circuit", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "for", "the", "ninth", "circuit", "five", "of", "the", "six", "judge", "in", "those", "case", "that", "hear", "those", "case", "approve", "the", "rule", "in", "the", "federal", "district", "court", "it", "be", "a", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "The -- in the Sixth Circuit rather seriously --", "start": 786.006, "stop": 788.902, "duration": 2.9, "cleanText": [["the", "in", "the", "sixth", "circuit", "rather", "seriously"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sir?", "start": 788.902, "stop": 790.915, "duration": 2.01, "cleanText": [["sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "I was rather interested to see that that was a Tennessee case that came from --", "start": 790.915, "stop": 794.089, "duration": 3.17, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "rather", "interested", "to", "see", "that", "that", "be", "a", "tennessee", "case", "that", "come", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It came up from the Western --", "start": 794.089, "stop": 794.879, "duration": 0.79, "cleanText": [["it", "come", "up", "from", "the", "western"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Bailey Brown, the District Judge Bailey Brown in the opinion in the Court of Appeals written by Chief Judge Harry Phillips, both are Tennessee lawyers.", "start": 794.879, "stop": 802.79, "duration": 7.91, "cleanText": [["bailey", "brown", "the", "district", "judge", "bailey", "brown", "in", "the", "opinion", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "write", "by", "chief", "judge", "harry", "phillips", "both", "be", "tennessee", "lawyer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 802.79, "stop": 803.167, "duration": 0.38, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "And then the three judges in the Ninth Circuit Court --", "start": 803.167, "stop": 805.432, "duration": 2.26, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "three", "judge", "in", "the", "ninth", "circuit", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course, were not Tennessee?", "start": 805.432, "stop": 806.326, "duration": 0.89, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "we", "be", "not", "tennessee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Were not Tennessee lawyers.", "start": 806.326, "stop": 807.329, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "not", "tennessee", "lawyer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 807.329, "stop": 809.419, "duration": 2.09, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you now what law was involved in the Ninth Circuit Case?", "start": 809.419, "stop": 815.426, "duration": 6.01, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "now", "what", "law", "be", "involve", "in", "the", "ninth", "circuit", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was a Court ruling, there was no federal statute involved.", "start": 815.426, "stop": 820.152, "duration": 4.73, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "court", "ruling", "there", "be", "no", "federal", "statute", "involve"]]}, {"text": "The District Court judge simply -- well, its quoted on page 8 of our brief.", "start": 820.152, "stop": 829.004, "duration": 8.85, "cleanText": [["the", "district", "court", "judge", "simply", "well", "it", "be", "quote", "on", "page", "of", "our", "brief"]]}, {"text": "The defendant wanted to -- well, the Court said that if the defendant was going to testify in his own behalf, he have to proceed all the other witnesses and the Court of Appeals said and I quote just a little bit from that says that, Trial Courts ruling seems to be a sensible approach to the problem of what to do with the party who is also a witness when the exclusion of witnesses is called for in order to prevent fabrication of testimony and cites Wigmore on evidence and goes on to say that there is no prejudice shown and the only connection we can think of the appellant was rendered incapable of tailoring his own testimony to fit in with what previously was said by other witnesses.", "start": 829.004, "stop": 877.406, "duration": 48.4, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "want", "to", "well", "the", "court", "say", "that", "if", "the", "defendant", "be", "go", "to", "testify", "in", "his", "own", "behalf", "he", "have", "to", "proceed", "all", "the", "other", "witness", "and", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "say", "and", "i", "quote", "just", "a", "little", "bit", "from", "that", "say", "that", "trial", "court", "s", "ruling", "seem", "to", "be", "a", "sensible", "approach", "to", "the", "problem", "of", "what", "to", "do", "with", "the", "party", "who", "be", "also", "a", "witness", "when", "the", "exclusion", "of", "witness", "be", "call", "for", "in", "order", "to", "prevent", "fabrication", "of", "testimony", "and", "cite", "wigmore", "on", "evidence", "and", "go", "on", "to", "say", "that", "there", "be", "no", "prejudice", "show", "and", "the", "only", "connection", "we", "can", "think", "of", "the", "appellant", "be", "render", "incapable", "of", "tailor", "his", "own", "testimony", "to", "fit", "in", "with", "what", "previously", "be", "say", "by", "other", "witness"]]}, {"text": "And beside the American jurisdictions that weve referred to, a number of English speaking jurisdictions have had this rule and still have it.", "start": 877.406, "stop": 887.038, "duration": 9.63, "cleanText": [["and", "beside", "the", "american", "jurisdiction", "that", "we", "have", "refer", "to", "a", "number", "of", "english", "speaking", "jurisdiction", "have", "have", "this", "rule", "and", "still", "have", "it"]]}, {"text": "And we refer in -- on pages 10 and 11 to -- a case from Alberta, Canada in which the Court said to be called as the first witness for the defense or that the accuse ought to be called as the first witness for the offense because otherwise its -- observation to the jury that the accused has called it or adopted his evidence that fit in with the evidence of the witnesses who proceeded him.", "start": 887.038, "stop": 914.157, "duration": 27.12, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "refer", "in", "on", "page", "and", "to", "a", "case", "from", "alberta", "canada", "in", "which", "the", "court", "say", "to", "be", "call", "as", "the", "first", "witness", "for", "the", "defense", "or", "that", "the", "accuse", "ought", "to", "be", "call", "as", "the", "first", "witness", "for", "the", "offense", "because", "otherwise", "its", "observation", "to", "the", "jury", "that", "the", "accuse", "have", "call", "it", "or", "adopt", "his", "evidence", "that", "fit", "in", "with", "the", "evidence", "of", "the", "witness", "who", "proceed", "him"]]}, {"text": "And we refer to an Australian case upholding the rule and I think significantly in England, a rule thats been a matter of practice since at least 1911, only recently in 1968 by the Court of Criminal Appeals in -- or the Court of Appeals in criminal division in England in a unanimous decision was made a Rule of Court for England and the Justice who wrote the opinion for that Court in 1968 said in part, the reason for this is obvious.", "start": 914.157, "stop": 951.026, "duration": 36.87, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "refer", "to", "an", "australian", "case", "uphold", "the", "rule", "and", "i", "think", "significantly", "in", "england", "a", "rule", "that", "be", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "practice", "since", "at", "least", "only", "recently", "in", "by", "the", "court", "of", "criminal", "appeal", "in", "or", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "in", "criminal", "division", "in", "england", "in", "a", "unanimous", "decision", "be", "make", "a", "rule", "of", "court", "for", "england", "and", "the", "justice", "who", "write", "the", "opinion", "for", "that", "court", "in", "say", "in", "part", "the", "reason", "for", "this", "be", "obvious"]]}, {"text": "Its that if they are to be permitted to hear the evidence, that is the defendants or other witnesses, they may be tempted to turn their own evidence and we get and I will get to this a bit later if I have the time.", "start": 951.026, "stop": 965.31, "duration": 14.28, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "that", "if", "they", "be", "to", "be", "permit", "to", "hear", "the", "evidence", "that", "be", "the", "defendant", "or", "other", "witness", "they", "may", "be", "tempt", "to", "turn", "their", "own", "evidence", "and", "we", "get", "and", "i", "will", "get", "to", "this", "a", "bit", "later", "if", "i", "have", "the", "time"]]}, {"text": "This shows the reason of a rationality of the rule and Mr. Summers saw the petitioner contends that under the Fourteenth Amendment its an unreasonable rule and we contend that its imminently a reasonable rule and this Court all said so that I referred to.", "start": 965.31, "stop": 986.501, "duration": 21.19, "cleanText": [["this", "show", "the", "reason", "of", "a", "rationality", "of", "the", "rule", "and", "mr", "summer", "saw", "the", "petitioner", "contend", "that", "under", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "it", "be", "an", "unreasonable", "rule", "and", "we", "contend", "that", "it", "be", "imminently", "a", "reasonable", "rule", "and", "this", "court", "all", "say", "so", "that", "i", "refer", "to"]]}, {"text": "So we have to take the position that the Tennessee Rule is a truth in testimonial law, a truth in testimonial law that it promotes truthful testimony that its a rational, a logical, a legitimate complement of the sequestration of witnesses rule.", "start": 986.501, "stop": 1004.814, "duration": 18.31, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "have", "to", "take", "the", "position", "that", "the", "tennessee", "rule", "be", "a", "truth", "in", "testimonial", "law", "a", "truth", "in", "testimonial", "law", "that", "it", "promote", "truthful", "testimony", "that", "it", "be", "a", "rational", "a", "logical", "a", "legitimate", "complement", "of", "the", "sequestration", "of", "witness", "rule"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think remarkably if the Court would look at the pages that Im going to refer you to now in the petitioners brief that there is a concession of rationality there.", "start": 1004.814, "stop": 1019.547, "duration": 14.73, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "remarkably", "if", "the", "court", "would", "look", "at", "the", "page", "that", "I", "be", "go", "to", "refer", "you", "to", "now", "in", "the", "petitioner", "s", "brief", "that", "there", "be", "a", "concession", "of", "rationality", "there"]]}, {"text": "So at page 9 of the petitioners brief, he says that the fact that a party may not be placed under the rule, that is the sequestration rule, was probably one of the chief reasons for the requirement.", "start": 1019.547, "stop": 1033.176, "duration": 13.63, "cleanText": [["so", "at", "page", "of", "the", "petitioner", "s", "brief", "he", "say", "that", "the", "fact", "that", "a", "party", "may", "not", "be", "place", "under", "the", "rule", "that", "be", "the", "sequestration", "rule", "be", "probably", "one", "of", "the", "chief", "reason", "for", "the", "requirement"]]}, {"text": "And then he says at page 9 that requiring the defendant to testify first if he testifies at all ensures that he will not be tempted to alter his own testimony after hearing other evidence presented in his behalf and the petitioner says further at pages 7 and 8 that the occasional readiness of the interested person to adopt his testimony when offered later to a victory rather than to a veracity so as to meet the necessities is laid opened by a file of witnesses is a rationale basis for the Tennessee statutes in question.", "start": 1033.176, "stop": 1073.812, "duration": 40.64, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "he", "say", "at", "page", "that", "require", "the", "defendant", "to", "testify", "first", "if", "he", "testify", "at", "all", "ensures", "that", "he", "will", "not", "be", "tempt", "to", "alter", "his", "own", "testimony", "after", "hear", "other", "evidence", "present", "in", "his", "behalf", "and", "the", "petitioner", "say", "far", "at", "page", "and", "that", "the", "occasional", "readiness", "of", "the", "interested", "person", "to", "adopt", "his", "testimony", "when", "offer", "later", "to", "a", "victory", "rather", "than", "to", "a", "veracity", "so", "as", "to", "meet", "the", "necessity", "be", "lay", "open", "by", "a", "file", "of", "witness", "be", "a", "rationale", "basis", "for", "the", "tennessee", "statutes", "in", "question"]]}, {"text": "And then finally at page 17 of the petitioners brief, the petitioner says, the purpose of this code section to ensure that a defendant not be tempted to color his version of the circumstances by hearing witnesses in favor prior to his own testimony is perhaps legitimate.", "start": 1073.812, "stop": 1094.509, "duration": 20.7, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "finally", "at", "page", "of", "the", "petitioner", "s", "brief", "the", "petitioner", "say", "the", "purpose", "of", "this", "code", "section", "to", "ensure", "that", "a", "defendant", "not", "be", "tempt", "to", "color", "his", "version", "of", "the", "circumstance", "by", "hear", "witness", "in", "favor", "prior", "to", "his", "own", "testimony", "be", "perhaps", "legitimate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick as I read that section of the petitioners brief, I had the feeling he was dealing very fairly with the arguments against him and felt nonetheless that this was a burden on the right.", "start": 1094.509, "stop": 1105.125, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "as", "i", "read", "that", "section", "of", "the", "petitioner", "s", "brief", "i", "have", "the", "feeling", "he", "be", "deal", "very", "fairly", "with", "the", "argument", "against", "him", "and", "felt", "nonetheless", "that", "this", "be", "a", "burden", "on", "the", "right"]]}, {"text": "He was asserting.", "start": 1105.125, "stop": 1105.816, "duration": 0.69, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "assert"]]}, {"text": "He certainly didnt concede that his point was invalid.", "start": 1105.816, "stop": 1108.905, "duration": 3.09, "cleanText": [["he", "certainly", "do", "not", "concede", "that", "his", "point", "be", "invalid"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "He said all of this things and I applaud him for his fairness, true.", "start": 1108.905, "stop": 1113.532, "duration": 4.63, "cleanText": [["he", "say", "all", "of", "this", "thing", "and", "i", "applaud", "him", "for", "his", "fairness", "true"]]}, {"text": "But the -- and he does view this as a burden and the state will say that that sometimes it may appear to be an inconvenience to the defendant but its an inconvenience to the state to have the limitation thats placed upon it.", "start": 1113.532, "stop": 1129.494, "duration": 15.96, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "and", "he", "do", "view", "this", "as", "a", "burden", "and", "the", "state", "will", "say", "that", "that", "sometimes", "it", "may", "appear", "to", "be", "an", "inconvenience", "to", "the", "defendant", "but", "it", "be", "an", "inconvenience", "to", "the", "state", "to", "have", "the", "limitation", "that", "be", "place", "upon", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick, you can say it was an inconvenience to the state in this case, was it?", "start": 1129.494, "stop": 1135.16, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "you", "can", "say", "it", "be", "an", "inconvenience", "to", "the", "state", "in", "this", "case", "be", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I think my point --", "start": 1135.16, "stop": 1135.807, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "my", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "It might remind you that the state offered to waive it?", "start": 1135.807, "stop": 1139.088, "duration": 3.28, "cleanText": [["it", "might", "remind", "you", "that", "the", "state", "offer", "to", "waive", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "True and I wasnt present at the trial.", "start": 1139.088, "stop": 1142.66, "duration": 3.57, "cleanText": [["true", "and", "i", "be", "not", "present", "at", "the", "trial"]]}, {"text": "The District Attorney General took care of the trial and this --", "start": 1142.66, "stop": 1145.317, "duration": 2.66, "cleanText": [["the", "district", "attorney", "general", "take", "care", "of", "the", "trial", "and", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, he did it, you dont contest that he did say it was all right with him.", "start": 1145.317, "stop": 1148.825, "duration": 3.51, "cleanText": [["well", "he", "do", "it", "you", "do", "not", "contest", "that", "he", "do", "say", "it", "be", "all", "right", "with", "him"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "True and I can only speculate that it really probably didnt make any difference to the state in this case because they have confessed (Voice Overlap).", "start": 1148.825, "stop": 1157.936, "duration": 9.11, "cleanText": [["true", "and", "i", "can", "only", "speculate", "that", "it", "really", "probably", "do", "not", "make", "any", "difference", "to", "the", "state", "in", "this", "case", "because", "they", "have", "confess", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But a number of other question is, when was the sequestration rule adopted in Tennessee?", "start": 1157.936, "stop": 1163.721, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["but", "a", "number", "of", "other", "question", "be", "when", "be", "the", "sequestration", "rule", "adopt", "in", "tennessee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "All might, its very ancient.", "start": 1163.721, "stop": 1165.836, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["all", "might", "it", "be", "very", "ancient"]]}, {"text": "I think its been in effect to all the way back as far as --", "start": 1165.836, "stop": 1168.216, "duration": 2.38, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "be", "in", "effect", "to", "all", "the", "way", "back", "as", "far", "as"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You keep saying that this is tied in it.", "start": 1168.216, "stop": 1170.098, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["you", "keep", "say", "that", "this", "be", "tie", "in", "it"]]}, {"text": "Nothing can be find anything in the statute that even hints that its tied in to the sequestration rule.", "start": 1170.098, "stop": 1176.337, "duration": 6.24, "cleanText": [["nothing", "can", "be", "find", "anything", "in", "the", "statute", "that", "even", "hint", "that", "it", "be", "tie", "in", "to", "the", "sequestration", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the statute was --", "start": 1176.337, "stop": 1176.602, "duration": 0.27, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "statute", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Or it was that the State of Tennessee in granting the defendant the right to testify put this limitation on.", "start": 1176.602, "stop": 1185.097, "duration": 8.49, "cleanText": [["or", "it", "be", "that", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "in", "grant", "the", "defendant", "the", "right", "to", "testify", "put", "this", "limitation", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats when the limitation was first put on.", "start": 1185.097, "stop": 1187.101, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "when", "the", "limitation", "be", "first", "put", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "So where do we get this and the reason for it was the reason that the prosecuting witness had to go first?", "start": 1187.101, "stop": 1194.019, "duration": 6.92, "cleanText": [["so", "where", "do", "we", "get", "this", "and", "the", "reason", "for", "it", "be", "the", "reason", "that", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "have", "to", "go", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It did not state it there but we have by judicial decision the requirement of the prosecuting witness so far.", "start": 1194.019, "stop": 1200.711, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "state", "it", "there", "but", "we", "have", "by", "judicial", "decision", "the", "requirement", "of", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "so", "far"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "So the prime side, isnt it?", "start": 1200.711, "stop": 1203.166, "duration": 2.45, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "prime", "side", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont know that Your Honor.", "start": 1203.166, "stop": 1205.588, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "that", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I think when it first came up that the Court ruled that way.", "start": 1205.588, "stop": 1210.479, "duration": 4.89, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "when", "it", "first", "come", "up", "that", "the", "court", "rule", "that", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You dont think its a matter of due process that the person entitled to control his witnesses as to when he puts on his proof and how he it puts it on.", "start": 1210.479, "stop": 1220.132, "duration": 9.65, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "due", "process", "that", "the", "person", "entitle", "to", "control", "his", "witness", "as", "to", "when", "he", "put", "on", "his", "proof", "and", "how", "he", "it", "put", "it", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont think its a matter of due process, Your Honor.", "start": 1220.132, "stop": 1223.028, "duration": 2.9, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "due", "process", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I think its a matter and in fact the number of Courts in the -- that Court rule simply as a procedure for regulating the order in that testimony.", "start": 1223.028, "stop": 1233.588, "duration": 10.56, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "and", "in", "fact", "the", "number", "of", "court", "in", "the", "that", "court", "rule", "simply", "as", "a", "procedure", "for", "regulate", "the", "order", "in", "that", "testimony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But would your case be different if the statute had said that all witnesses who are going to testify must testify first?", "start": 1233.588, "stop": 1244.106, "duration": 10.52, "cleanText": [["but", "would", "your", "case", "be", "different", "if", "the", "statute", "have", "say", "that", "all", "witness", "who", "be", "go", "to", "testify", "must", "testify", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont understand the question.", "start": 1244.106, "stop": 1247.509, "duration": 3.4, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "understand", "the", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, you said the prosecuting witness has to go first?", "start": 1247.509, "stop": 1250.953, "duration": 3.44, "cleanText": [["well", "you", "say", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "have", "to", "go", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats true Your Honor, if hes going to testify, he has to testify first.", "start": 1250.953, "stop": 1256.768, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["that", "have", "true", "your", "honor", "if", "he", "have", "go", "to", "testify", "he", "have", "to", "testify", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Statute --", "start": 1256.768, "stop": 1257.392, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I think its proposed in this committee recommendation.", "start": 1257.392, "stop": 1260.785, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "it", "be", "propose", "in", "this", "committee", "recommendation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well you equate the prosecuting witness with the defendant and I suggest that thats improper.", "start": 1260.785, "stop": 1267.791, "duration": 7.01, "cleanText": [["well", "you", "equate", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "with", "the", "defendant", "and", "i", "suggest", "that", "that", "be", "improper"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sir?", "start": 1267.791, "stop": 1268.294, "duration": 0.5, "cleanText": [["sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I suggest that the prosecuting witness and the defendant are not at equal positions.", "start": 1268.294, "stop": 1274.664, "duration": 6.37, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "that", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "and", "the", "defendant", "be", "not", "at", "equal", "position"]]}, {"text": "As I understand that this is the Donald L. Brooks versus the State of Tennessee.", "start": 1274.664, "stop": 1278.578, "duration": 3.91, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "understand", "that", "this", "be", "the", "donald", "l", "brook", "versus", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is, yes.", "start": 1278.578, "stop": 1280.119, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont even know who the prosecuting witness was?", "start": 1280.119, "stop": 1283.14, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "even", "know", "who", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, he was a man who had his a store.", "start": 1283.14, "stop": 1284.773, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["no", "he", "be", "a", "man", "who", "have", "his", "a", "store"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I mean he was in the party.", "start": 1284.773, "stop": 1288.753, "duration": 3.98, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "he", "be", "in", "the", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well --", "start": 1288.753, "stop": 1288.959, "duration": 0.21, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "The state is the party.", "start": 1288.959, "stop": 1290.11, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "be", "the", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The state is the party.", "start": 1290.11, "stop": 1291.347, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "be", "the", "party"]]}, {"text": "Thats true but I dont think its correct to say that the prosecuting witness has no interest in the outcome, well, when hes been robbed and he wants to see justice there and he is the chief witness to the state.", "start": 1291.347, "stop": 1303.288, "duration": 11.94, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "true", "but", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "correct", "to", "say", "that", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "have", "no", "interest", "in", "the", "outcome", "well", "when", "he", "be", "be", "robbed", "and", "he", "want", "to", "see", "justice", "there", "and", "he", "be", "the", "chief", "witness", "to", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick, the petitioner concedes that there is a tie in between the sequestration rule --", "start": 1303.288, "stop": 1308.087, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "the", "petitioner", "concede", "that", "there", "be", "a", "tie", "in", "between", "the", "sequestration", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, he does.", "start": 1308.087, "stop": 1308.141, "duration": 0.05, "cleanText": [["yes", "he", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And this rule, doesnt he?", "start": 1308.141, "stop": 1309.439, "duration": 1.3, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "rule", "do", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, he does.", "start": 1309.439, "stop": 1311.46, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["yes", "he", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "General Kendrick, is the -- are witnesses sequestered in all criminal cases routinely in Tennessee even if no motion is made to do so?", "start": 1311.46, "stop": 1323.207, "duration": 11.75, "cleanText": [["general", "kendrick", "be", "the", "be", "witness", "sequester", "in", "all", "criminal", "case", "routinely", "in", "tennessee", "even", "if", "no", "motion", "be", "make", "to", "do", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Its not a matter of law, the judge routinely says that parties want the rule and rather routine as they say we do.", "start": 1323.207, "stop": 1329.998, "duration": 6.79, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "matter", "of", "law", "the", "judge", "routinely", "say", "that", "party", "want", "the", "rule", "and", "rather", "routine", "as", "they", "say", "we", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do the parties want the rule?", "start": 1329.998, "stop": 1331.467, "duration": 1.47, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "party", "want", "the", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1331.467, "stop": 1331.74, "duration": 0.27, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That we do and then -- until its done?", "start": 1331.74, "stop": 1332.799, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["that", "we", "do", "and", "then", "until", "its", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "That goes in there.", "start": 1332.799, "stop": 1335.327, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["that", "go", "in", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "What happens if the defendant waived the rule?", "start": 1335.327, "stop": 1338.33, "duration": 3, "cleanText": [["what", "happen", "if", "the", "defendant", "waive", "the", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The sequestration rule?", "start": 1338.33, "stop": 1339.944, "duration": 1.61, "cleanText": [["the", "sequestration", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, the --", "start": 1339.944, "stop": 1342.074, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["yes", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, if the --", "start": 1342.074, "stop": 1342.826, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Cant you reply?", "start": 1342.826, "stop": 1344.116, "duration": 1.29, "cleanText": [["can", "not", "you", "reply"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "If the state -- both parties have to waive the rule and then the rule is not in effect.", "start": 1344.116, "stop": 1348.84, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "state", "both", "party", "have", "to", "waive", "the", "rule", "and", "then", "the", "rule", "be", "not", "in", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the statute is?", "start": 1348.84, "stop": 1349.968, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "statute", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The statute still is in effect, thats right.", "start": 1349.968, "stop": 1352.425, "duration": 2.46, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "still", "be", "in", "effect", "that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "How do you meet that?", "start": 1352.425, "stop": 1355.12, "duration": 2.69, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "you", "meet", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont know that we have to meet it.", "start": 1355.12, "stop": 1361.35, "duration": 6.23, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "that", "we", "have", "to", "meet", "it"]]}, {"text": "The judges though will apply the statute unless its waived by the state and sometimes the state offers to waive it in and then the defendant may go on when he wants to, agrees to waive.", "start": 1361.35, "stop": 1372.554, "duration": 11.2, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "though", "will", "apply", "the", "statute", "unless", "it", "be", "waive", "by", "the", "state", "and", "sometimes", "the", "state", "offer", "to", "waive", "it", "in", "and", "then", "the", "defendant", "may", "go", "on", "when", "he", "want", "to", "agree", "to", "waive"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was the rule invoked in this case, the sequestration rule?", "start": 1372.554, "stop": 1378.181, "duration": 5.63, "cleanText": [["be", "the", "rule", "invoke", "in", "this", "case", "the", "sequestration", "rule"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I do not remember that, it was invoked.", "start": 1378.181, "stop": 1384.421, "duration": 6.24, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "remember", "that", "it", "be", "invoke"]]}, {"text": "And we refer the Court at pages 13 and 14 to the decision which requires this to the prosecution --", "start": 1384.421, "stop": 1390.422, "duration": 6, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "refer", "the", "court", "at", "page", "and", "to", "the", "decision", "which", "require", "this", "to", "the", "prosecution"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is this in your own brief now, 13 and 14?", "start": 1390.422, "stop": 1392.571, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "in", "your", "own", "brief", "now", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, Im sorry Your Honor, Mr. Chief Justice, pages 13 and 14 of our brief.", "start": 1392.571, "stop": 1398.17, "duration": 5.6, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "I", "be", "sorry", "your", "honor", "mr", "chief", "justice", "page", "and", "of", "our", "brief"]]}, {"text": "We refer to the judicial requirement that the prosecution or the prosecuting witness go on first.", "start": 1398.17, "stop": 1406.693, "duration": 8.52, "cleanText": [["we", "refer", "to", "the", "judicial", "requirement", "that", "the", "prosecution", "or", "the", "prosecuting", "witness", "go", "on", "first"]]}, {"text": "I hope weve been able to demonstrate that what we have in Tennessee here then is not a unique requirement but even if it was unique requirement that would make it unconstitutional.", "start": 1406.693, "stop": 1418.287, "duration": 11.59, "cleanText": [["i", "hope", "we", "have", "be", "able", "to", "demonstrate", "that", "what", "we", "have", "in", "tennessee", "here", "then", "be", "not", "a", "unique", "requirement", "but", "even", "if", "it", "be", "unique", "requirement", "that", "would", "make", "it", "unconstitutional"]]}, {"text": "Under our federal system of government the states are -- as Mr. Justice Brandeis said are laboratories in which experimentation may be made and referred to an opinion by Justice Blackmun in McKeiver versus Pennsylvania on page 15 of our brief to the same effect.", "start": 1418.287, "stop": 1440.795, "duration": 22.51, "cleanText": [["under", "our", "federal", "system", "of", "government", "the", "state", "be", "as", "mr", "justice", "brandeis", "say", "be", "laboratory", "in", "which", "experimentation", "may", "be", "make", "and", "refer", "to", "an", "opinion", "by", "justice", "blackmun", "in", "mckeiver", "versus", "pennsylvania", "on", "page", "of", "our", "brief", "to", "the", "same", "effect"]]}, {"text": "So, we submit that a judge should not vote against this rule of procedure simply because he disagrees with it as a matter of policy or I would personally prefer an ultimate procedure and we refer to the Court to Justice Harlans opinion in McGautha versus California in 1971 decision which we cite in our brief, 402 U.S. 183 and 221 and we refer the Court also to Mr. Justice Stewarts concurring opinion in Spencer versus U.S. also cited in our brief --", "start": 1440.795, "stop": 1482.739, "duration": 41.94, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "submit", "that", "a", "judge", "should", "not", "vote", "against", "this", "rule", "of", "procedure", "simply", "because", "he", "disagree", "with", "it", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "policy", "or", "i", "would", "personally", "prefer", "an", "ultimate", "procedure", "and", "we", "refer", "to", "the", "court", "to", "justice", "harlan", "s", "opinion", "in", "mcgautha", "versus", "california", "in", "decision", "which", "we", "cite", "in", "our", "brief", "us", "and", "and", "we", "refer", "the", "court", "also", "to", "mr", "justice", "stewart", "s", "concur", "opinion", "in", "spencer", "versus", "us", "also", "cite", "in", "our", "brief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats against Texas?", "start": 1482.739, "stop": 1484.887, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "against", "texas"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Against Texas, 385 U.S. 352 and 567, thank you sir.", "start": 1484.887, "stop": 1492.99, "duration": 8.1, "cleanText": [["against", "texas", "us", "and", "thank", "you", "sir"]]}, {"text": "Now in the time which may remains me, Id like to turn to the petitioners objections to the Tennessee statute and I understand from his oral argument yesterday that he does conceive that the Sixth Amendment question is not before the Court in view of the limited grant of certiorari.", "start": 1492.99, "stop": 1512.939, "duration": 19.95, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "the", "time", "which", "may", "remain", "me", "I", "would", "like", "to", "turn", "to", "the", "petitioner", "objection", "to", "the", "tennessee", "statute", "and", "i", "understand", "from", "his", "oral", "argument", "yesterday", "that", "he", "do", "conceive", "that", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "question", "be", "not", "before", "the", "court", "in", "view", "of", "the", "limited", "grant", "of", "certiorari"]]}, {"text": "His Fifth Amendment argument as I gather is that this rule in some way infringes upon the defendants right to remain silent and by the way rather remarkably, I think later on he argues under the Tennessee Constitution Provision that it also infringes his right to be heard but now he says it infringes upon his right to silent.", "start": 1512.939, "stop": 1540.271, "duration": 27.33, "cleanText": [["his", "fifth", "amendment", "argument", "as", "i", "gather", "be", "that", "this", "rule", "in", "some", "way", "infringe", "upon", "the", "defendant", "s", "right", "to", "remain", "silent", "and", "by", "the", "way", "rather", "remarkably", "i", "think", "later", "on", "he", "argue", "under", "the", "tennessee", "constitution", "provision", "that", "it", "also", "infringe", "his", "right", "to", "be", "hear", "but", "now", "he", "say", "it", "infringe", "upon", "his", "right", "to", "silent"]]}, {"text": "But at page 16 of his brief he concedes, Nor does it deny a defendant to their right to remain silent.", "start": 1540.271, "stop": 1549.475, "duration": 9.2, "cleanText": [["but", "at", "page", "of", "his", "brief", "he", "concede", "nor", "do", "it", "deny", "a", "defendant", "to", "their", "right", "to", "remain", "silent"]]}, {"text": "His point seems to be that because he has to go on first, if he goes on at all that this is cutting down on his privilege or chilling it in some way and that it makes it more difficult.", "start": 1549.475, "stop": 1564.251, "duration": 14.78, "cleanText": [["his", "point", "seem", "to", "be", "that", "because", "he", "have", "to", "go", "on", "first", "if", "he", "go", "on", "at", "all", "that", "this", "be", "cut", "down", "on", "his", "privilege", "or", "chill", "it", "in", "some", "way", "and", "that", "it", "make", "it", "more", "difficult"]]}, {"text": "The states answer to this is, that petitioner and his counsel ought to know before they get to trial. But the testimony will be what the witnesses will say and the desirability for waiving the right to remain silent and taking the stand in its own behalf.", "start": 1564.251, "stop": 1582.759, "duration": 18.51, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "answer", "to", "this", "be", "that", "petitioner", "and", "his", "counsel", "ought", "to", "know", "before", "they", "get", "to", "trial"], ["but", "the", "testimony", "will", "be", "what", "the", "witness", "will", "say", "and", "the", "desirability", "for", "waive", "the", "right", "to", "remain", "silent", "and", "take", "the", "stand", "in", "its", "own", "behalf"]]}, {"text": "Our feeling about is that the only thing that is limited as far as the defendant is concerned is the opportunity to trim or to color or to falsify his testimony to conform of what the other witnesses on his side have said and this is what this case is uniformly say that we have all ready referred the Court to.", "start": 1582.759, "stop": 1603.009, "duration": 20.25, "cleanText": [["our", "feel", "about", "be", "that", "the", "only", "thing", "that", "be", "limit", "as", "far", "as", "the", "defendant", "be", "concern", "be", "the", "opportunity", "to", "trim", "or", "to", "color", "or", "to", "falsify", "his", "testimony", "to", "conform", "of", "what", "the", "other", "witness", "on", "his", "side", "have", "say", "and", "this", "be", "what", "this", "case", "be", "uniformly", "say", "that", "we", "have", "all", "ready", "refer", "the", "court", "to"]]}, {"text": "The defendant says that in choosing to testify more making at charge at the beginning of his proof.", "start": 1603.009, "stop": 1610.597, "duration": 7.59, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "say", "that", "in", "choose", "to", "testify", "more", "making", "at", "charge", "at", "the", "beginning", "of", "his", "proof"]]}, {"text": "He then hazards himself through the cross examination or subjects himself to the hazards of cross examination, indeed he does.", "start": 1610.597, "stop": 1619.125, "duration": 8.53, "cleanText": [["he", "then", "hazard", "himself", "through", "the", "cross", "examination", "or", "subject", "himself", "to", "the", "hazard", "of", "cross", "examination", "indeed", "he", "do"]]}, {"text": "But every witness who goes on the stand subjects himself to that hazard and the defendant will be subjected to that hazard regardless of when he takes the stand.", "start": 1619.125, "stop": 1630.316, "duration": 11.19, "cleanText": [["but", "every", "witness", "who", "go", "on", "the", "stand", "subject", "himself", "to", "that", "hazard", "and", "the", "defendant", "will", "be", "subject", "to", "that", "hazard", "regardless", "of", "when", "he", "take", "the", "stand"]]}, {"text": "Another point he makes is that choosing to testify the beginning of this proof is a matter which should be left to his unfretted freedom.", "start": 1630.316, "stop": 1640.937, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["another", "point", "he", "make", "be", "that", "choose", "to", "testify", "the", "beginning", "of", "this", "proof", "be", "a", "matter", "which", "should", "be", "leave", "to", "his", "unfretted", "freedom"]]}, {"text": "Now, we point out at pages 18 and 19 of our brief that the defendant has the unfretted freedom to testify.", "start": 1640.937, "stop": 1652.499, "duration": 11.56, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "point", "out", "at", "page", "and", "of", "our", "brief", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "the", "unfretted", "freedom", "to", "testify"]]}, {"text": "He only -- he is restricted as to when he can testify and we cite them McGautha versus California to the effect that its not unconstitutional simply to make him exercise a difficult choice.", "start": 1652.499, "stop": 1670.35, "duration": 17.85, "cleanText": [["he", "only", "he", "be", "restrict", "as", "to", "when", "he", "can", "testify", "and", "we", "cite", "them", "mcgautha", "versus", "california", "to", "the", "effect", "that", "it", "be", "not", "unconstitutional", "simply", "to", "make", "him", "exercise", "a", "difficult", "choice"]]}, {"text": "I would like to move quickly to his Fourteenth Amendment argument which our view is in three parts.", "start": 1670.35, "stop": 1678.214, "duration": 7.86, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "move", "quickly", "to", "his", "fourteenth", "amendment", "argument", "which", "our", "view", "be", "in", "three", "part"]]}, {"text": "One is that it imposes a burden upon him.", "start": 1678.214, "stop": 1683.533, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["one", "be", "that", "it", "impose", "a", "burden", "upon", "him"]]}, {"text": "It does into some extent limit him but again, I remind the Court that hes not restricted from testifying.", "start": 1683.533, "stop": 1692.007, "duration": 8.47, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "into", "some", "extent", "limit", "him", "but", "again", "i", "remind", "the", "court", "that", "he", "be", "not", "restrict", "from", "testify"]]}, {"text": "He may testify.", "start": 1692.007, "stop": 1693.561, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["he", "may", "testify"]]}, {"text": "The Court though will require him to testify first.", "start": 1693.561, "stop": 1697.251, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "though", "will", "require", "him", "to", "testify", "first"]]}, {"text": "But there is no reason why he has to hear the testimony of his own witnesses before he takes the stand.", "start": 1697.251, "stop": 1703.274, "duration": 6.02, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "no", "reason", "why", "he", "have", "to", "hear", "the", "testimony", "of", "his", "own", "witness", "before", "he", "take", "the", "stand"]]}, {"text": "A lot of good reasons why he has to hear the testimony of the witnesses of the state against him but he ought to know before his own witnesses take the stand what they are going to say.", "start": 1703.274, "stop": 1712.074, "duration": 8.8, "cleanText": [["a", "lot", "of", "good", "reason", "why", "he", "have", "to", "hear", "the", "testimony", "of", "the", "witness", "of", "the", "state", "against", "him", "but", "he", "ought", "to", "know", "before", "his", "own", "witness", "take", "the", "stand", "what", "they", "be", "go", "to", "say"]]}, {"text": "Now, if they crack up on the cross examination then it would be beneficial to him to be able to get back on the stand and to rehabilitate the case I suppose.", "start": 1712.074, "stop": 1722.153, "duration": 10.08, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "they", "crack", "up", "on", "the", "cross", "examination", "then", "it", "would", "be", "beneficial", "to", "him", "to", "be", "able", "to", "get", "back", "on", "the", "stand", "and", "to", "rehabilitate", "the", "case", "i", "suppose"]]}, {"text": "The second --", "start": 1722.153, "stop": 1722.791, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["the", "second"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, lets assume that the defendant wants to call a police officer like he did in this case and the police officer hasnt testified?", "start": 1722.791, "stop": 1734.644, "duration": 11.85, "cleanText": [["well", "let", "us", "assume", "that", "the", "defendant", "want", "to", "call", "a", "police", "officer", "like", "he", "do", "in", "this", "case", "and", "the", "police", "officer", "have", "not", "testify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, he has opened to him an opportunity before taking -- discover deposition in advance in the trial and know -- and to know under oath what the officer is going to say.", "start": 1734.644, "stop": 1745.571, "duration": 10.93, "cleanText": [["well", "he", "have", "open", "to", "him", "an", "opportunity", "before", "take", "discover", "deposition", "in", "advance", "in", "the", "trial", "and", "know", "and", "to", "know", "under", "oath", "what", "the", "officer", "be", "go", "to", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the criminal case in Tennessee?", "start": 1745.571, "stop": 1747.887, "duration": 2.32, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "criminal", "case", "in", "tennessee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats my remembrance of it Your Honor.", "start": 1747.887, "stop": 1751.081, "duration": 3.19, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "my", "remembrance", "of", "it", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I would not like to be held to that but that thats the way I remember it.", "start": 1751.081, "stop": 1756.309, "duration": 5.23, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "not", "like", "to", "be", "hold", "to", "that", "but", "that", "that", "be", "the", "way", "i", "remember", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You mean in Tennessee you can get depositions with the governments witnesses?", "start": 1756.309, "stop": 1760.719, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["you", "mean", "in", "tennessee", "you", "can", "get", "deposition", "with", "the", "government", "s", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thats certainly true in civil cases and --", "start": 1760.719, "stop": 1762.947, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "certainly", "true", "in", "civil", "case", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Im talking about criminal cases.", "start": 1762.947, "stop": 1764.02, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "talk", "about", "criminal", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I know you are and I just have to say I dont have a clear -- I am not entirely sure of that.", "start": 1764.02, "stop": 1769.394, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "you", "be", "and", "i", "just", "have", "to", "say", "i", "do", "not", "have", "a", "clear", "i", "be", "not", "entirely", "sure", "of", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Assume that isnt so and the --", "start": 1769.394, "stop": 1771.171, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["assume", "that", "be", "not", "so", "and", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 1771.171, "stop": 1772.134, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You want to call the Chief of Police.", "start": 1772.134, "stop": 1774.633, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["you", "want", "to", "call", "the", "chief", "of", "police"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "But he may go out --", "start": 1774.633, "stop": 1775.426, "duration": 0.79, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "may", "go", "out"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Its been under subpoena by the state to come to trial when the state have chosen not to put him on so the defendant ask the Court I would like to put him on and treat him as a hostile witness and the Court said, sorry, if you call him, hes your witness.", "start": 1775.426, "stop": 1791.046, "duration": 15.62, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "be", "under", "subpoena", "by", "the", "state", "to", "come", "to", "trial", "when", "the", "state", "have", "choose", "not", "to", "put", "him", "on", "so", "the", "defendant", "ask", "the", "court", "i", "would", "like", "to", "put", "him", "on", "and", "treat", "him", "as", "a", "hostile", "witness", "and", "the", "court", "say", "sorry", "if", "you", "call", "him", "he", "be", "your", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "If all those things are done.", "start": 1791.046, "stop": 1792.866, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["if", "all", "those", "thing", "be", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1792.866, "stop": 1794.274, "duration": 1.41, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "And whats the question?", "start": 1794.274, "stop": 1795.055, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["and", "what", "be", "the", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "The question is you really dont know where you stand, do you,, on your defense?", "start": 1795.055, "stop": 1798.784, "duration": 3.73, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "be", "you", "really", "do", "not", "know", "where", "you", "stand", "do", "you", "on", "your", "defense"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1798.784, "stop": 1799.067, "duration": 0.28, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "You dont know where you stand on the defense.", "start": 1799.067, "stop": 1800.56, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "know", "where", "you", "stand", "on", "the", "defense"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was the case in this case, that was the situation in this case.", "start": 1800.56, "stop": 1804.855, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "case", "in", "this", "case", "that", "be", "the", "situation", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I dont remember that all of those things were true about him having been subpoenaed --", "start": 1804.855, "stop": 1811.275, "duration": 6.42, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "remember", "that", "all", "of", "those", "thing", "we", "be", "true", "about", "him", "have", "be", "subpoenaed"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "The chief was under subpoena by the state.", "start": 1811.275, "stop": 1815.492, "duration": 4.22, "cleanText": [["the", "chief", "be", "under", "subpoena", "by", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "He had to testify.", "start": 1815.492, "stop": 1817.425, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "to", "testify"]]}, {"text": "He asked the Court to let him cross examine and said, no, if you call him hes your witness.", "start": 1817.425, "stop": 1824.474, "duration": 7.05, "cleanText": [["he", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "let", "him", "cross", "examine", "and", "say", "no", "if", "you", "call", "him", "he", "be", "your", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, thats right, if he called him, he would have been the witness of the defendant but we dont conceive that that in any way denies this defendant of his Fourteenth Amendment or due process rise and may I just tell --", "start": 1824.474, "stop": 1839.135, "duration": 14.66, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "right", "if", "he", "call", "him", "he", "would", "have", "be", "the", "witness", "of", "the", "defendant", "but", "we", "do", "not", "conceive", "that", "that", "in", "any", "way", "deny", "this", "defendant", "of", "his", "fourteenth", "amendment", "or", "due", "process", "rise", "and", "may", "i", "just", "tell"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the fact is though that you really sometimes cant know what your defense is -- what the witnesses you want to call, that you are going to risk calling and really going to say (Voice Overlap) hold up under cross examination.", "start": 1839.135, "stop": 1851.39, "duration": 12.26, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "fact", "be", "though", "that", "you", "really", "sometimes", "can", "not", "know", "what", "your", "defense", "be", "what", "the", "witness", "you", "want", "to", "call", "that", "you", "be", "go", "to", "risk", "call", "and", "really", "go", "to", "say", "voice", "overlap", "hold", "up", "under", "cross", "examination"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "You certainly should be able to interview your witnesses in advance unless you make the spot decision after you get to court that you are going to call some witness you have thought of calling to the court and I dont know of any reason why this defendant in this case did not have interviewed the chief or anybody else that he wanted to out of a trial.", "start": 1851.39, "stop": 1868.352, "duration": 16.96, "cleanText": [["you", "certainly", "should", "be", "able", "to", "interview", "your", "witness", "in", "advance", "unless", "you", "make", "the", "spot", "decision", "after", "you", "get", "to", "court", "that", "you", "be", "go", "to", "call", "some", "witness", "you", "have", "think", "of", "call", "to", "the", "court", "and", "i", "do", "not", "know", "of", "any", "reason", "why", "this", "defendant", "in", "this", "case", "do", "not", "have", "interview", "the", "chief", "or", "anybody", "else", "that", "he", "want", "to", "out", "of", "a", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Kendrick, didnt you say an answer to an early question of mine that if in fact the police officer had covered a matter in the way that the defendant had the elected to first testify had not gone into that it would have been up to the trial judges discretion whether the defendant might not have been recalled?", "start": 1868.352, "stop": 1886.132, "duration": 17.78, "cleanText": [["mr", "kendrick", "do", "not", "you", "say", "an", "answer", "to", "an", "early", "question", "of", "mine", "that", "if", "in", "fact", "the", "police", "officer", "have", "cover", "a", "matter", "in", "the", "way", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "the", "elect", "to", "first", "testify", "have", "not", "go", "into", "that", "it", "would", "have", "be", "up", "to", "the", "trial", "judge", "s", "discretion", "whether", "the", "defendant", "might", "not", "have", "be", "recall"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "To allow him to be recalled to the stand after he wants to testify and Your Honor may I -- I have seen the red light.", "start": 1886.132, "stop": 1892.755, "duration": 6.62, "cleanText": [["to", "allow", "him", "to", "be", "recall", "to", "the", "stand", "after", "he", "want", "to", "testify", "and", "your", "honor", "may", "i", "i", "have", "see", "the", "red", "light"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your time is up but if you -- you may draw into a conclusion which you can go on.", "start": 1892.755, "stop": 1896.055, "duration": 3.3, "cleanText": [["your", "time", "be", "up", "but", "if", "you", "you", "may", "draw", "into", "a", "conclusion", "which", "you", "can", "go", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would like to make a concluding statement if it please the Court.", "start": 1896.055, "stop": 1898.868, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "make", "a", "concluding", "statement", "if", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do it briefly.", "start": 1898.868, "stop": 1901.206, "duration": 2.34, "cleanText": [["do", "it", "briefly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Robert E. Kendrick", "textObjs": [{"text": "The only other point that I havent covered and I will cover it in one sentence, concerns the matter of the state constitution.", "start": 1901.206, "stop": 1911.284, "duration": 10.08, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "other", "point", "that", "i", "have", "not", "cover", "and", "i", "will", "cover", "it", "in", "one", "sentence", "concern", "the", "matter", "of", "the", "state", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "Its contended that the Tennessee Courts have misconstrued the statute in holding that it is not unconstitutional on its state constitution and I would like to refer the Court throughout the cases that we cite and filed proposition of our brief to the effect that that is decisions of this Court that that is really a matter for the state courts to decide whether state statute violate the state constitution and its not a federal question for this Court to be concerned with.", "start": 1911.284, "stop": 1940.545, "duration": 29.26, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "contend", "that", "the", "tennessee", "court", "have", "misconstrue", "the", "statute", "in", "hold", "that", "it", "be", "not", "unconstitutional", "on", "its", "state", "constitution", "and", "i", "would", "like", "to", "refer", "the", "court", "throughout", "the", "case", "that", "we", "cite", "and", "file", "proposition", "of", "our", "brief", "to", "the", "effect", "that", "that", "be", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "that", "that", "be", "really", "a", "matter", "for", "the", "state", "court", "to", "decide", "whether", "state", "statute", "violate", "the", "state", "constitution", "and", "it", "be", "not", "a", "federal", "question", "for", "this", "court", "to", "be", "concern", "with"]]}, {"text": "In conclusion, I would simply say that the defendant has not made out a case that runs constitutionality of this truth and testimonial law and we do ask the Court in the words of Justice Cardozo to keep the balance true.", "start": 1940.545, "stop": 1957.922, "duration": 17.38, "cleanText": [["in", "conclusion", "i", "would", "simply", "say", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "not", "make", "out", "a", "case", "that", "run", "constitutionality", "of", "this", "truth", "and", "testimonial", "law", "and", "we", "do", "ask", "the", "court", "in", "the", "word", "of", "justice", "cardozo", "to", "keep", "the", "balance", "true"]]}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1957.922, "stop": 1958.105, "duration": 0.18, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Kendrick.", "start": 1958.105, "stop": 1961.394, "duration": 3.29, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "kendrick"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Summers.", "start": 1961.394, "stop": 1966.173, "duration": 4.78, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.", "start": 1966.173, "stop": 1968.753, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "In a very short time I have remaining, I would like to elaborate on some questions that was asked by justices yesterday.", "start": 1968.753, "stop": 1976.502, "duration": 7.75, "cleanText": [["in", "a", "very", "short", "time", "i", "have", "remain", "i", "would", "like", "to", "elaborate", "on", "some", "question", "that", "be", "ask", "by", "justice", "yesterday"]]}, {"text": "The first one that pertain to question by the Chief --Mr. Chief Justice in regard the question of offer of proof.", "start": 1976.502, "stop": 1982.45, "duration": 5.95, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "one", "that", "pertain", "to", "question", "by", "the", "chief", "mr", "chief", "justice", "in", "regard", "the", "question", "of", "offer", "of", "proof"]]}, {"text": "Your Honor, yesterday you inquired as to whether I should have made an offer proof and in this matter which you felt would possibly affect the record more fully.", "start": 1982.45, "stop": 1991.229, "duration": 8.78, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "yesterday", "you", "inquire", "as", "to", "whether", "i", "should", "have", "make", "an", "offer", "proof", "and", "in", "this", "matter", "which", "you", "felt", "would", "possibly", "affect", "the", "record", "more", "fully"]]}, {"text": "I would only say that in the law in the State of Tennessee is that if an entire land of testimony is excluded or an entire witnesses testimony is excluded then it is not necessary to make an offer of proof under our laws of the State of Tennessee to protect an appeal.", "start": 1991.229, "stop": 2006.289, "duration": 15.06, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "only", "say", "that", "in", "the", "law", "in", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "be", "that", "if", "an", "entire", "land", "of", "testimony", "be", "exclude", "or", "an", "entire", "witness", "testimony", "be", "exclude", "then", "it", "be", "not", "necessary", "to", "make", "an", "offer", "of", "proof", "under", "our", "law", "of", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "to", "protect", "an", "appeal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is it permitted?", "start": 2006.289, "stop": 2008.231, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "permit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is it permitted?", "start": 2008.231, "stop": 2009.075, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "permit"]]}, {"text": "Yes, sir.", "start": 2009.075, "stop": 2009.359, "duration": 0.28, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "To make an offer?", "start": 2009.359, "stop": 2010.586, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["to", "make", "an", "offer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it should be within discretion of the courts.", "start": 2010.586, "stop": 2012.744, "duration": 2.16, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "should", "be", "within", "discretion", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "There has been a recent decision in the criminal court which allows you to make a -- in the criminal courts theyve allowed you to make an offer of proof.", "start": 2012.744, "stop": 2020.54, "duration": 7.8, "cleanText": [["there", "have", "be", "a", "recent", "decision", "in", "the", "criminal", "court", "which", "allow", "you", "to", "make", "a", "in", "the", "criminal", "court", "they", "have", "allow", "you", "to", "make", "an", "offer", "of", "proof"]]}, {"text": "But that was -- decision came after this case was tried.", "start": 2020.54, "stop": 2023.898, "duration": 3.36, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "decision", "come", "after", "this", "case", "be", "try"]]}, {"text": "In regards to Mr. Rehn -- Mr. Justice Rehnquists question yesterday, I believe that in discussion at the time for rebuttal and surrebutal got jumbled up and I would like to say that it is my contention under the law that the scope that the defendant, if he was not allowed to testify and put on other witnesses, the state then put on rebuttal witnesses to testify to rebut his witnesses that he could testify as surrebutal witnesses but the scope of his surrebutal would be limited to those matters which had been brought out on the states rebuttal.", "start": 2023.898, "stop": 2057.551, "duration": 33.65, "cleanText": [["in", "regard", "to", "mr", "rehn", "mr", "justice", "rehnquist", "s", "question", "yesterday", "i", "believe", "that", "in", "discussion", "at", "the", "time", "for", "rebuttal", "and", "surrebutal", "get", "jumble", "up", "and", "i", "would", "like", "to", "say", "that", "it", "be", "my", "contention", "under", "the", "law", "that", "the", "scope", "that", "the", "defendant", "if", "he", "be", "not", "allow", "to", "testify", "and", "put", "on", "other", "witness", "the", "state", "then", "put", "on", "rebuttal", "witness", "to", "testify", "to", "rebut", "his", "witness", "that", "he", "could", "testify", "as", "surrebutal", "witness", "but", "the", "scope", "of", "his", "surrebutal", "would", "be", "limit", "to", "those", "matter", "which", "have", "be", "bring", "out", "on", "the", "state", "rebuttal"]]}, {"text": "Now, we say that that does not alleviate the problem created by the statute.", "start": 2057.551, "stop": 2066.266, "duration": 8.72, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "say", "that", "that", "do", "not", "alleviate", "the", "problem", "create", "by", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "If he could be a surrebutal witness because there are matters which certainly we would like to -- should be submitted to the court.", "start": 2066.266, "stop": 2072.414, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "could", "be", "a", "surrebutal", "witness", "because", "there", "be", "matter", "which", "certainly", "we", "would", "like", "to", "should", "be", "submit", "to", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Now, in this matter in regards to Mr. Justice Blackmuns question as to privilege as to yesterday, if this Court should declare the statute unconstitutional, it would be the burden upon the state to show beyond a reasonable doubt under the far holdings of this Court that the area was promised and not prejudicial.", "start": 2072.414, "stop": 2090.529, "duration": 18.11, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "this", "matter", "in", "regard", "to", "mr", "justice", "blackmun", "s", "question", "as", "to", "privilege", "as", "to", "yesterday", "if", "this", "court", "should", "declare", "the", "statute", "unconstitutional", "it", "would", "be", "the", "burden", "upon", "the", "state", "to", "show", "beyond", "a", "reasonable", "doubt", "under", "the", "far", "holding", "of", "this", "court", "that", "the", "area", "be", "promise", "and", "not", "prejudicial"]]}, {"text": "Now, our position is that we contend that nothing can be more prejudicial than a statute which will restrict or deny a defendant from testifying his own behalf and if this statute is per se prejudicial.", "start": 2090.529, "stop": 2103.548, "duration": 13.02, "cleanText": [["now", "our", "position", "be", "that", "we", "contend", "that", "nothing", "can", "be", "more", "prejudicial", "than", "a", "statute", "which", "will", "restrict", "or", "deny", "a", "defendant", "from", "testify", "his", "own", "behalf", "and", "if", "this", "statute", "be", "per", "se", "prejudicial"]]}, {"text": "We say that the defendant has a right to testify under the authority of a -- absolute right under Ferguson versus Georgia and in closing I would respectfully say that we think that --", "start": 2103.548, "stop": 2115.723, "duration": 12.18, "cleanText": [["we", "say", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "a", "right", "to", "testify", "under", "the", "authority", "of", "a", "absolute", "right", "under", "ferguson", "versus", "georgia", "and", "in", "closing", "i", "would", "respectfully", "say", "that", "we", "think", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You think a -- you think that was Ferguson held?", "start": 2115.723, "stop": 2118.664, "duration": 2.94, "cleanText": [["you", "think", "a", "you", "think", "that", "be", "ferguson", "hold"]]}, {"text": "Is that a constitutional (Voice Overlap).", "start": 2118.664, "stop": 2119.688, "duration": 1.02, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "a", "constitutional", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think -- I read it by implication that that was the way that I read the decision this -- that --", "start": 2119.688, "stop": 2124.812, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "i", "read", "it", "by", "implication", "that", "that", "be", "the", "way", "that", "i", "read", "the", "decision", "this", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was the right to counsel?", "start": 2124.812, "stop": 2126.125, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "right", "to", "counsel"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, yes it was.", "start": 2126.125, "stop": 2127.916, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "yes", "it", "be"]]}, {"text": "But I felt the reading -- hat was the interpretation that applying Ferguson to this case that Donald Brooks has an absolute right to testify in a criminal case and that it -- that any that the state -- the statute State of Tennessee is restricting that right and that is the argument.", "start": 2127.916, "stop": 2147.373, "duration": 19.46, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "felt", "the", "reading", "hat", "be", "the", "interpretation", "that", "apply", "ferguson", "to", "this", "case", "that", "donald", "brook", "have", "an", "absolute", "right", "to", "testify", "in", "a", "criminal", "case", "and", "that", "it", "that", "any", "that", "the", "state", "the", "statute", "state", "of", "tennessee", "be", "restrict", "that", "right", "and", "that", "be", "the", "argument"]]}, {"text": "In closing, I would say that the decisions of Bell versus Mississippi and of Shipp which have been cited which the dissenting opinion of Judge McAlister we think present a logical and analytical approach to this to the problem, we respectfully urge the Court to reverse the conviction and declare the statute unconstitutional.", "start": 2147.373, "stop": 2166.797, "duration": 19.42, "cleanText": [["in", "closing", "i", "would", "say", "that", "the", "decision", "of", "bell", "versus", "mississippi", "and", "of", "shipp", "which", "have", "be", "cite", "which", "the", "dissent", "opinion", "of", "judge", "mcalister", "we", "think", "present", "a", "logical", "and", "analytical", "approach", "to", "this", "to", "the", "problem", "we", "respectfully", "urge", "the", "court", "to", "reverse", "the", "conviction", "and", "declare", "the", "statute", "unconstitutional"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Summers just one question.", "start": 2166.797, "stop": 2170.333, "duration": 3.54, "cleanText": [["mr", "summer", "just", "one", "question"]]}, {"text": "You just said made claim to an absolute constitutional right to testify on behalf of the defendant.", "start": 2170.333, "stop": 2177.649, "duration": 7.32, "cleanText": [["you", "just", "say", "make", "claim", "to", "an", "absolute", "constitutional", "right", "to", "testify", "on", "behalf", "of", "the", "defendant"]]}, {"text": "Suppose the defendant at the opening of a case after the jury was selected, defendants counsel said now before the minds of the jury are poisoned, influenced by the prosecutions testimony, I would like an opportunity to put my defendants, the accused on the stand and have him tell his story to this jury.", "start": 2177.649, "stop": 2205.148, "duration": 27.5, "cleanText": [["suppose", "the", "defendant", "at", "the", "opening", "of", "a", "case", "after", "the", "jury", "be", "select", "defendant", "s", "counsel", "say", "now", "before", "the", "mind", "of", "the", "jury", "be", "poison", "influence", "by", "the", "prosecution", "testimony", "i", "would", "like", "an", "opportunity", "to", "put", "my", "defendant", "the", "accuse", "on", "the", "stand", "and", "have", "him", "tell", "his", "story", "to", "this", "jury"]]}, {"text": "Would you think he would an absolute right as part of his absolute right to testify that you claim to be heard first before the state is heard from?", "start": 2205.148, "stop": 2216.301, "duration": 11.15, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "think", "he", "would", "an", "absolute", "right", "as", "part", "of", "his", "absolute", "right", "to", "testify", "that", "you", "claim", "to", "be", "hear", "first", "before", "the", "state", "be", "hear", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, you do not Your Honor.", "start": 2216.301, "stop": 2217.872, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["no", "you", "do", "not", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I respectfully say that the burden --", "start": 2217.872, "stop": 2220.183, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["i", "respectfully", "say", "that", "the", "burden"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you concede that that might be a very helpful thing to a defendant sometimes to be able to get to the jury first before they have heard the prosecutions witnesses?", "start": 2220.183, "stop": 2230.062, "duration": 9.88, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "concede", "that", "that", "might", "be", "a", "very", "helpful", "thing", "to", "a", "defendant", "sometimes", "to", "be", "able", "to", "get", "to", "the", "jury", "first", "before", "they", "have", "hear", "the", "prosecution", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, I would say no because they urge the presumption of innocence in the burden of proof to prove guilt is upon the state (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 2230.062, "stop": 2236.09, "duration": 6.03, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "i", "would", "say", "no", "because", "they", "urge", "the", "presumption", "of", "innocence", "in", "the", "burden", "of", "proof", "to", "prove", "guilt", "be", "upon", "the", "state", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "He acknowledged the tactical matter.", "start": 2236.09, "stop": 2239.31, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["he", "acknowledge", "the", "tactical", "matter"]]}, {"text": "You suggest that it would never be to the advantage of the defendant to have that opportunity to reach the jury with his story first?", "start": 2239.31, "stop": 2247.856, "duration": 8.55, "cleanText": [["you", "suggest", "that", "it", "would", "never", "be", "to", "the", "advantage", "of", "the", "defendant", "to", "have", "that", "opportunity", "to", "reach", "the", "jury", "with", "his", "story", "first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Jerry H. Summers", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, being in the heat of battle in many trials I would say and knowing how your trial can change, I would be reluctant as the trial counsel to -- until I had heard some of the proof.", "start": 2247.856, "stop": 2260.014, "duration": 12.16, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "be", "in", "the", "heat", "of", "battle", "in", "many", "trial", "i", "would", "say", "and", "know", "how", "your", "trial", "can", "change", "i", "would", "be", "reluctant", "as", "the", "trial", "counsel", "to", "until", "i", "have", "hear", "some", "of", "the", "proof"]]}, {"text": "I make the decision quite frequently as to whether my -- to put my client on the stand by the manner in which the states approve and I say would be first -- it would be a very infrequent case which I would put my client on because we do not have full discovery in the State of Tennessee, we have very limited in criminal procedure and I would be very hesitant to put my client on the stand to -- since to kill the prosecution there might be a very rare case in which it might be such as a matter of incest in which you - it would be uncorroborated testimony of an accomplice and with the state had very limited -- a very weak case.", "start": 2260.014, "stop": 2296.381, "duration": 36.37, "cleanText": [["i", "make", "the", "decision", "quite", "frequently", "as", "to", "whether", "my", "to", "put", "my", "client", "on", "the", "stand", "by", "the", "manner", "in", "which", "the", "state", "approve", "and", "i", "say", "would", "be", "first", "it", "would", "be", "a", "very", "infrequent", "case", "which", "i", "would", "put", "my", "client", "on", "because", "we", "do", "not", "have", "full", "discovery", "in", "the", "state", "of", "tennessee", "we", "have", "very", "limit", "in", "criminal", "procedure", "and", "i", "would", "be", "very", "hesitant", "to", "put", "my", "client", "on", "the", "stand", "to", "since", "to", "kill", "the", "prosecution", "there", "might", "be", "a", "very", "rare", "case", "in", "which", "it", "might", "be", "such", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "incest", "in", "which", "you", "it", "would", "be", "uncorroborated", "testimony", "of", "an", "accomplice", "and", "with", "the", "state", "have", "very", "limited", "a", "very", "weak", "case"]]}, {"text": "But I would be very reluctant as to file counsel to employ such a tactic because I can foresee it could backfire very readily.", "start": 2296.381, "stop": 2304.138, "duration": 7.76, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "would", "be", "very", "reluctant", "as", "to", "file", "counsel", "to", "employ", "such", "a", "tactic", "because", "i", "can", "foresee", "it", "could", "backfire", "very", "readily"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Summers.", "start": 2304.138, "stop": 2305.088, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "summer"]]}, {"text": "Thank you, Mr. Kendrick.", "start": 2305.088, "stop": 2306.257, "duration": 1.17, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "kendrick"]]}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 2306.257, "stop": 2307.463, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Burger Court", "arguedOn": "Mar  21 - 22, 1972", "petitioner": "Brooks", "respondent": "Tennessee", "docket": "71-5313", "citation": "406US605(1972)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/406/605", "lowerCourt": "State appellate court", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "Jun 7, 1972"}